title: roseanna, banana kabana
directions: In blender, add 1 cup small ice cubes and remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Garnish with cherry.

title: grandmother's cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg and beat well. Add milk or orange juice, then flour.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; chop fine.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 2-quart dish 30 minutes at 375° or until set.
You can use fresh broccoli.

title: sausage pesto casserole
directions: Cook and drain pasta as directed on package in 3-quart sauce pan.
Set aside.
Spray same saucepan with non-stick cooking spray; heat over medium heat.
Cook sausage in saucepan about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until brown; drain.
Stir pesto sauce, water and pasta into sausage.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sausage is no longer pink in center.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven in greased 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Then add eggs, corn meal, water, vanilla, salt, and pecans.
Mix well and pour into pie shells.

title: mrs. christopher's cheese potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash well. Add 1 1/2 cups of the Cheddar cheese, eggs, milk, salt and onions, blending thoroughly.
Pour in casserole and top with the remaining cheese.
Cook at 350° until brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be stored uncooked in deep freeze or refrigerator until time to be used.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift with flour the baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Slice apples and place in large bowl.
Add sugar and mix.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Blend melted butter and eggs; add to apples.
Add flour mixture and mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour in a 10 x 14-inch pan, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake in preheated oven for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water, add syrup, gradually add gelatin mixture to mayonnaise and blend well.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pineapple and cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Stew chicken until tender, remove from bones and cut into small pieces.
Reserve broth.
Using 4 to 6 tablespoons fat, fry onion, celery, cabbage and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soy sauce until vegetables look brown.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken broth slightly, add vegetables, mushrooms and a little more soy sauce.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
For 6 in family, use 2 pounds spaghetti.
Cook until tender, then wash in cold water until it doesn't feel starchy.
Drain.
Fry in patties in deep fat.
When brown on both sides, remove from fat and put on plate.
Sprinkle shredded chicken over pattie, then dip broth and vegetables over patties.
Serve while hot.

title: thanksgiving eve spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, saving 1 to 2 tablespoons of drippings. Saute onions and garlic in drippings.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Add sauce.
Add paste to onions and garlic.
Add sugar and spices. Stir together well.
Add ground beef; stir well.
Let simmer for at least 3 hours.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: french steak
directions: Saute steak in oil (or without) until brown. Add onion.
Stir in carrots.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In saucepan, slowly mix broth and cornstarch. Cook until slightly thickened (stirring constantly).
Slowly pour in beaten egg.
Stir once very gently. Remove from heat and top with onion. Serves 4.

title: no knead dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/3 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, Crisco and salt until just warm.
Add to dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Add egg.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, then high speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Place in a greased bowl; turn once. Cover; let rise until doubled, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; turn out and cover.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into desired shape.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add egg yolks; reserve egg whites for later.
Mix well. Dredge fruit and nuts in 1 cup of flour, then add to mixture.
Stir in remaining flour.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold egg whites into mixture.
Place in baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This will make one large or 2 small cakes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in syrup, salt and vanilla.
Stir in chips, nuts and bourbon. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Do not use deep dish pie crusts.
Serve warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: herbed lamb chops
directions: Place chops in shallow dish.
Combine ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Pour over chops, cover and refrigerate 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Place chops on unheated rack of broiler.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Brush with marinade, turn and broil 3 to 5 minutes more.

title: taco dip
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Salt and pepper.
In 10 x 10-inch pan, spread refried beans.
Put hamburger over top.
Chop chiles and put over beans and hamburger.
Spread cheese and taco sauce over.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.
Immediately spread with sour cream, chopped green olives and chopped green onions.
Serve on nacho flavored chips.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Set 2 racks in the middle and upper thirds of the oven and preheat to 350°.

In a medium bowl, stir the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, oats and pecans together with a whisk or fork. In a large bowl, beat the butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar together for 30 seconds until blended.
Beat in the egg until smooth and barely fluffy.
With mixer running on medium high, drizzle in the maple syrup and vanilla until incorporated.
Turn the mixer down to its lowest setting and gradually add the flour-oatmeal mixture.
Blend just to combine, then mix in the chocolate chips.
Drop walnut-sized balls of dough onto a nonstick or parchment-lined cookie sheet at 3 inch intervals.
With moistened fingers, flatten and round out the cookies a little. Bake for 9 minutes, turning the pan once for even baking.
The cookies are done when they are lightly browned on top.
Set the cookie sheets on a rack to cool.
Yield:
about 36 cookies.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and flour for 20 minutes.
Add one egg at a time. Add flavor.
Fold in 7-Up and lemon flavoring.
Cook in tube pan (large).
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: catsup
directions: Cook tomatoes or juice, paprika, sugar, salt, onions and vinegar together a bit.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour, then thicken with clear jell.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix beans and taco mix together.
Place on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over bean and taco mix.
Grate cheese and put on top.
Cook at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add shortening to pan of hot applesauce until it dissolves. Remove from stove.
Add soda dissolved in water to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir slowly by hand until ingredients are well mixed.
Add flour.
Place in a tube pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in large pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn oven back to 350° and cook for approximately 2 hours, stirring at least 3 times.
Stir for the last time about 25 minutes before done.

title: waffles
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together well, then add next 2 ingredients.
Stir well and add next 2 ingredients.
Pour mixture onto grids of a preheated lightly greased waffle baker.
Use a fork to remove waffles.
Sprinkle baked waffles with confectioners sugar.

title: peachy pork picante
directions: Coat pork with seasoning and brown in oil. Add both salsa and preserves to skillet; mix well. Cover and lower heat. Simmer gently 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned german dumplings
directions: Boil water with oil and salt.
Then add flour all at once. Stir until it leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat and cool. Add 1 egg and stir until absorbed, then add the other egg the same way.
Drop by small spoonfuls into your favorite vegetable soup and cover tightly.
Let cook for about 15 minutes.
Makes 16 dumplings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt
Velveeta	cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Pour over cooked broccoli.	Sprinkle crackers on top and pour 1/2 stick of melted butter over all.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes and cook until done, then drain.
Cut up onion and bacon bits.
Put oil and vinegar in a bowl.
Add potatoes and stir potatoes together; serve while warm.

title: country crust bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in more flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover with damp towel; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Form into 2 loaves or 2 dozen rolls.
Put in greased pans.
Brush with salad oil.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake loaves for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake rolls 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: club crunchies
directions: Bring margarine, butter and sugar to a boil.
Separate crackers on foil on a jelly roll sheet.
Sprinkle mixture over crackers and top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Separate with a knife.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in pan and heat until jello dissolves; let cool. Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pecans. When jello has cooled, add cottage cheese mixture to it; mix together well and put in refrigerator until congealed.

title: potatoes mornay
directions: Melt butter; add flour; cook until bubbly.
Add milk; cook until smooth, using a whisk.
Boil 1 minute.
Cut cheese in small pieces; beat into hot cream sauce, using electric beater at medium speed about 10 to 12 minutes.
Add beer, a little at a time.
Keep beating until of good, thick consistency.
Boil potatoes; peel and chop.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Mix by hand.
Use generous amount of sauce, as you don't want potatoes to be dry.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake in 350 degree oven until bubbly.
Any leftover sauce is good over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 days.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let set to marinate.
Tasty with raw vegetables.

title: molly's tomato salad
directions: Mix in bowl all ingredients in order.
Mix thoroughly.
Add extra saltines, if needed.
Garnish with whole saltines and cherry tomatoes.
Chill and serve.

title: overnight coffee ring
directions: Use a one piece angel food cake pan.

title: pork satay singapore
directions: Cut 2 unpared medium zucchini lengthwise in half.
Cook covered in 1 inch boiling salted water for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with dill weed.
Serves 4.

title: maple nut chiffon
directions: Beat in large bowl until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture over whites, while folding in with rubber spatula.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: streusel filled coffee cake(makes three 8-inch coffee cakes.)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; cut in shortening until it looks like fine cornmeal.
Beat eggs; add milk and vanilla.
Mix this with other ingredients just until all is mixed together.

title: jelly-jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar set 2 or 3 hours, then boil until done. Add strawberry Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Put into glasses.

title: artichoke dip(microwave)
directions: Drain artichoke hearts from can.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Place in microwave 2 minutes. Ready to serve.
Use Wheat Thins as well as any crackers you prefer.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients and chill.

title: seafood salad
directions: Dice or flake crab meat; add other ingredients.
Toss well. Chill.

title: peaches and cream pudding cake
directions: Use juice from peaches for cake mix.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Place peaches in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Then pudding, then pour cake mix over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Good with Cool Whip.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: In medium saucepan, bring 2 quarts water to a boil.
Add celery, carrot, onion, salt and bay leaf.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add shrimp.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes after water returns to a simmer or until the shrimp are opaque in center.
Drain.

title: hagerstown beans and rice
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Add scallions and ham; saute for 1 minute.
Add kidney beans and rice.
Season with salt, pepper and hot sauce to taste.
Toss until heated through.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and corn.
Fry in deep fat. Serve with syrup.

title: julie's potato salad
directions: Note:
If desired, add 6 1/2 ounces tuna, drained and flaked.

title: stained glass windows
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips; let cool slightly.
Add colored marshmallows and mix to cover with chocolate, being careful not to stir too much.
You do not want marshmallows to melt.
Divide mixture onto 4 pieces of waxed paper and roll each into a log.
Chill.
Remove from waxed paper and cut into 1-inch slices.

title: sour cream cut-outs
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream oleo, sugar, egg, vanilla and sour cream.
Combine two mixtures together.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 6 minutes at 375°.
Ice cookies when cooled.

title: candied orange peel
directions: Simmer sugar, water and zest of 1 orange until thickened. When peel is well glazed, separate and let cool on wax paper. Works equally well with lemon

title: cherry cheesecake mousse
directions: Whip together cheesecake filling and Cool Whip.
Take large flat baking dish (13 x 9-inch); sprinkle graham cracker crust package in bottom of dish.
Put 1/2 of cheesecake filling mixture on top of crumbs; level out.
Put 1/2 of cherry pie filling next; level out.
Place remainder of cheesecake filling; level out. Follow with remainder of cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Whisk together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt; set aside. Combine orange juice, oil, vanilla, yogurt, egg and blueberries.
Combine all ingredients together until moistened. Spray muffin cups and bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Muffins can be sprinkled with sugar before baking or can be iced with powdered sugar icing after baking.

title: mom's frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, salt, sugar and pineapple.
Add nuts, cherries and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in 9 x 13 x 2-inch container (greased with mayonnaise).
Cover and freeze. Put in refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving.
Slice and serve. Delicious and kids love it.

title: corn bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients together and sift into bowl.
Add eggs, milk and salad oil; mix until no lumps.
Place in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan; bake in heated oven at 400° for about 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine cornstarch and cinnamon in small pan.
Stir in apple juice.
Heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add to sliced apples.
Turn into pastry lined pan; dot with margarine.
Top with pastry.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add next 5 ingredients; saute until onions are just brown. Stir in chicken and remove from stove.

title: potato patties
directions: Chop onion and green pepper. Mix all ingredients except oil. Shape into 6 patties. Brown patties on both sides in just enough oil to keep from sticking.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Blend together juice, pudding and Cool Whip until smooth.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.

title: chocolate crackle cookies
directions: Combine sugar and oil in a large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate. Blend well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into mixture.
Add nuts and stir.
Sift powdered sugar on waxed paper.
Roll dough in small balls, then in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Make yellow cake.
When done, right from the oven and still hot, poke holes on top of cake.
Use back of knife or spoon, then pour pineapple over cake.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine the ingredients one at a time, beating well.
Pour batter into a large preheated greased skillet.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and chill for 2 hours before serving. Makes 1 1/4 cups of dressing.

title: quick cooking italian spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef together with onions and bell pepper.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except spaghetti.
Stir, blend, cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
May need to add a little water. Then boil dry spaghetti in salted water, uncovered.
Drain when tender.
Dip out extra fat from meat mixture.
Add spaghetti and stir.
Ready to serve.
Serves 6 people.

title: seafood antipasto
directions: Mix all ingredients into a boiler; simmer for 1 hour on lowest heat. Cool, then refrigerate. Serve on your favorite crackers (i.e., Ritz, Breedans).

title: glorified walnut roast
directions: Grind nuts, frozen peas and onion.
Add to other ingredients. Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marshmallow meringue
directions: Cut marshmallows in small pieces.
Fold into well-beaten egg whites.
Spread over pie.
Bake at 300°
for approximately 12 minutes.

title: mountain cherry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with ice.
Makes 25 servings.

title: bernie's pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, Italian seasoning and garlic powder together.
Spread evenly in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, scallions and green or red pepper.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated.
Serve hot with deli-style tortilla chips.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger with taco seasoning; drain.
Layer meat with refried beans, cheese, beans and chips.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 20 minutes.
Garnish with olives, sour cream, tomatoes and guacamole.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and sugar and vanilla well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Beat the cream cheese and sugar well; it should be creamy.
Blend in Cool Whip and spread evenly on graham cracker crust.
Spread cherry or blueberry pie filling over top of mixture and refrigerate.

title: light bread
directions: (Use a large Tupperware bowl.)
Put flour in bowl; make a well.
Scald milk, cool with water.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and yeast.
Pour liquid into well.
Do not stir.
Seal the bowl and whisper air.
Leave until seal pops up, usually takes 1 hour. Melt oleo, pour over dough.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Add enough flour until not sticky.
Seal again and leave set until seal pops off.
Make into rolls, bread or cinnamon rolls.
Bake at 400°.

title: coffee ice cream parfait
directions: Crush macaroons and mix into softened ice cream; fold in coffee liqueur and Cool Whip.
Put in parfait glasses; cover with foil and freeze.

title: hot oyster surprise
directions: Shell and clean oysters; put in pot with 1 cup water, lemon juice and half of the salt; simmer about 5 minutes.
Soak the onions in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water with 1/2 of the salt for about 5 minutes.
Drain well and saute in oil about 3 minutes. Then add to oysters; add vinegar, allspice, pepper, garlic, jalapeno peppers and 1 tablespoon jalapeno juice.
Cover and let stand 24 hours.
Serve with crackers and Tabasco sauce or other hot red sauce.

title: grecian chicken
directions: Wash and dry the chicken.
Brown well in oil in a heavy pan. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix tomato sauce, olives, and cinnamon.
Combine chicken and sauce in a covered oven dish.
Bake at 325° (gas 3) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning occasionally. Chicken is done when meat falls away from the bone.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: crackle top molasses cookies
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the remaining ingredients.
Stir in with the first mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: crockpot potato soup
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in crockpot. Cook on low for 7-8 hours. 30 minutes before serving, add milk and cheese; stir. Serve with French bread.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix together and roll in logs.
Chill.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: custard peach pie
directions: Slice peaches and arrange in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with sugar.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, eggs, 1 cup sugar, vanilla and flour with a fork or wire whisk.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 425° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Cook a few minutes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Spread cream cheese in pie plate.
Add crab meat; save a few pieces of crabmeat to put on top.
Then pour cocktail sauce over crabmeat.
Sprinkle the remaining crabmeat on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: witches' brew
directions: In the top of a double boiler, beat egg yolks well.
Add the milk, 3/4 cup of sugar and salt.
Cook over simmering water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Beat the egg whites until frothy; add 1/4 cup of sugar and continue beating until stiff. Whip the cream and pour into whites.
Pour cooled custard over all and gently fold until blended.
Gently stir in nectar, brandy and Triple Sec.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, beat it with a whisk, then pour into punch bowl.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream oleo and flour.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.
Blend peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly (save some for top).
Add cream cheese to mixture; beat until smooth.
Spread onto cooled crust. Prepare pudding by box instructions.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with remaining peanut butter crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put 1/2 mixture in pan. Add cheese.
Pour over rest of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a large saucepan, mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add approximately 3 tablespoons of water (just enough to make mixture wet).
Over medium heat, add butter and 2 cups of milk.
As butter starts to melt, turn heat to low and constantly stir.
Add more milk as needed to make mixture creamy or to desired thickness for gravy.
Serve over biscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll into balls; dip in sugar.
Bake 350 degrees.

title: grilled "apple pie"
directions: Slice apples to 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Butter both sides of bread.
Place apples and bread on charcoal grill on medium flame. Turn over when slightly brown.
Place bread on serving dish, followed by apples. Add the vanilla ice cream. Sprinkle with more cinnamon. Serve immediately.

title: sugarless applesauce raisin muffins
directions: Beat
together	the
egg,
oil and applesauce.	Add dry ingredients;
beat	well.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon batter into greased and
floured
muffin pans.	Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25	minutes,
or
until firm and brown.
Cool on wire rack. Delicious topped with cream cheese.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs
plus 5 tablespoons water; pour over rhubarb and stir.
Put in pie shell.
Dot with butter or margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt and add to eggs. Stir in vanilla, melted butter and buttermilk.
Bake in two 9-inch unbaked pie crusts for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes two pies that can be frozen after baking.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain grease.
Add enchilada sauce and soups until warm.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 bag of chips.
Pour mixture over chips. Top with cheese and then add other 1/2 bag of chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherub crab croquettes
directions: Melt the butter in a small pan; add the flour and cook over low heat.
Add the milk and cook until the mixture thickens.
Set aside.
Mix the crab meat with the parsley, onion, lemon juice, 2 eggs, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, hot pepper sauce and dry mustard.
Add the cooled cream sauce and shape into 3-inch long croquettes.
Beat 3 eggs and salt together in a bowl.
Dip each croquette in bread crumbs, then in beaten eggs and then in bread crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until brown.
Makes 1 dozen croquettes.

title: marinated cauliflower salad
directions: Early in the day or the day before serving, combine first 7 ingredients.
Cauliflower should be sliced and stirred into the rest.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Drain and slice olives and chop the green pepper.
Line salad bowl with Boston lettuce and spoon salad into bowl.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla in a large bowl at high speed until moist and crumbly and mixture begins to gather around beater. Stir in flour until blended.

title: butter creams candy
directions: Whip together butter, cream cheese and vanilla.
Gradually add confectioners sugar.
Chill.
Shape into balls and put on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill again.
In top of double boiler melt chips and Crisco.
Dip butter cream balls into chocolate. Set onto wax paper.
Keep chilled.

title: baked stuffed jumbo shrimp
directions: Place in pan with little water; this prevents shrimp from drying.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
This mixture is sufficient to stuff 12 jumbo shrimp.

title: savory stuffed peppers
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and onions; drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper.
Set aside.
Cut tops off peppers, remove seeds.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers. Place in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish and bake covered for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together.
Form balls and brown.
Pour a sauce of tomato or mushroom soup over meat balls and cook until done.

title: chili cobbler
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, 1 can water and chili mix to meat.
Salt to taste, let simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Press 5 to 6 crescent rolls on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with sides.
Spoon in chili.
Cover with shredded cheese, top with remaining rolls.
Bake according to crescent roll package.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients for the batter.
Mix the brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans separately; set aside.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Alternate batter and nut mixture until all batter is used, ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let cake cool 10 minutes, then turn upside down.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend together dry ingredients.
Put eggs, oil and pumpkin in mixer.
Blend well and add dry ingredients.
Put in stem or Bundt cake pan and cook at 350° for about 1 hour or until the cake leaves side of pan or bounces back at the touch of a finger.

title: blueberry jello dessert
directions: Stir together in pan the blackberry jello, hot water and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Then mix together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Put on top of jello.
Refrigerate when done.

title: mexican bean pot
directions: Boil beans 2 minutes and soak 1 hour or overnight.
Fry bacon half done; add fat to bean water and boil gently 2 hours.
Drain. Mix all ingredients except bacon, coffee and onion.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Pour coffee over beans, bacon and onion slices. Bake 20 minutes longer at 400°.

title: microwave stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Place mushrooms on plate; microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Chop stems; combine with onion in a covered casserole dish.
"Nuke" for 4 minutes.
Add cream cheese, bread crumbs and ham or bacon.
Add salt and pepper to taste; top mushrooms with mixture.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery until potatoes are done.
Add cream, butter, salt and pepper, then mix up flour and milk. Pour in and let thicken.

title: highland oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Beat butter, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in water. Add sifted ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in chopped nuts and raisins.
Stir in oats, one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Top with pecan half.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash. Combine beef, cooked rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Pile mixture into peppers and place in large baking dish. Pour tomato sauce over each pepper.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake in moderate (350°) oven for 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally.

title: new potato, pasta and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot (not boiling).
Add onion, cook 5 to 6 minutes or until partially cooked, stirring occasionally.
Stir in asparagus, bell pepper, oregano, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in cooked pasta; cook until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Let stand until cheese is melted.

title: bubbles
directions: *Distilled water works best.

title: old fashion egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in sugar, salt, nutmeg and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 40 minutes in hot oven at 450° for first 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° to finish baking.

title: hamburger dill pickles
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and salt.
In each quart jar put cucumbers, dill, 1/4 onion, 1/4 garlic and 1/2 stalk celery.
Pour brine over cucumbers.
Set in cold pack canners and cover with cold water.
Bring to boil and turn off heat.
Do not cook.

title: ding bats
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and dates over low heat until hard ball stage forms.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped pecans and the Rice Krispies.
Powder hands with confectioners sugar and roll into balls.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Slice a thin layer off top of each tomato.
Using a small spoon, carefully scoop out and discard pulp.
Invert tomatoes. Drain on paper towel.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Combine the shortening. brown sugar and eggs, mixing well.
Add the sour milk.
Sift the flour, soda and salt together and stir into the shortening mixture.
Mix in the pecans, cherries, and dates.
Drop the dough by teaspoonsful two inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in heated oven set at 350 for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: quick and easy soup
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain well.
Add cream of mushroom soup and chicken; heat slowly until bubbling, then reduce heat. Cook for 5 minutes; add salt and pepper.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: party crab mousse
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until blended.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to soup.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and put into a greased mold.
Chill overnight.
Serves 24.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Spoon in one container of Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: turnip greens and red potatoes
directions: Put greens in large pot. The greens cook down but to begin, you will need to push them down to get all into the pot. Add thinly sliced potatoes and cook until done. Remove potatoes and greens and save the broth.

title: pan-roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut each in half.
In skillet, melt butter with oil.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until browned on all sides.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes until fork-tender.
Makes 2 servings.

title: purple cow
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve immediately.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Dice ham.

In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and brown sugar. With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in diced ham and shredded cheese. Stir in milk just until mixture forms soft dough that leaves side of bowl.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Knead 6 to 8 strokes to mix thoroughly.
With floured rolling pin, roll dough into a 9 x 7-inch rectangle. With floured knife, cut dough lengthwise into 3 strips, then cut each strip crosswise into 4 pieces.
With pancake turner, place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden. Makes 12.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple; keep juice.
Slice grapes in half.
Add to pineapple juice the flour and sugar; cook to thicken and cool. Add to all remaining ingredients.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, salad oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla.
Then in separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to first mixture and beat well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab seafood casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese, crab meat, eggs and butter well.
Add flour and baked spinach souffle and mix well.
Fold in Cheddar cheese. Pour into buttered 12 x 8 x 1-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven until knife comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Note:
If using seasoned stuffing mix, omit herbs and salt.

title: sweet 'n saucy glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients
in small sauce pan.
Heat over low, stir occasionally until jelly melts.
Brush on chicken or ribs.

title: sourdough bread (from starter)
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water and let it stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar, eggs and starter.
Gradually add flour mixed with salt.
Cover bowl with a damp towel and let dough rise until doubled.
Knead on floured board until satiny. Shape into 1 large loaf or 2 smaller loaves.
Set on a cookie sheet to bake or put in greased bread pans.
Make diagonal slashes on top of bread and cover.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough, about 1 cup.
Roll very thin on floured surface; let stand 20 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch wide strips or let children make creative shapes; let dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup or salted boiling water, uncovered, about 10 minutes.

title: jonda's very best tomato casserole
directions: Add the sauteed onions to tomatoes along with brown sugar and basil.
Cut bread in small cubes.
In a greased casserole dish, put a layer of tomato mixture, layer of bread and cheese; repeat. Cut the bacon in small pieces and spread on top layer.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 325°.
Put under broiler to crisp bacon.
More or less bread is used, depending upon the juiciness of the tomatoes.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Roll water chestnuts in brown sugar.
Wrap with 1/2 piece of bacon. Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: omelet in a muffin
directions: Stir the egg, water, basil, ham and onion together.
Pour into hot skillet and cook until glossy.
Add cheese.
In small bowl, stir together the dressing and mustard.
Spread on one half of cooked muffin.
Spoon egg mixture on and make sandwich.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture, alternating with milk.
Mix well.
Add poppy seed and mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in greased Bundt pan.
Serve with strawberry butter.

title: pecan bourbon candy
directions: Cream 1/2 cup of butter.
Add sugar and liquor alternately, beating until thick and smooth.
Shape mixture into half teaspoon size balls.
Press a pecan half on each side of ball and chill 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs with milk and gradually beat in flour, salt and baking powder. Beat until smooth. Holding the opening of a funnel closed with your finger, fill the funnel with batter.

Open the end of the funnel and allow dough to run out in a stream into deep hot fat (375° on frying thermometer), moving funnel around starting at the center of pan and swirling batter outward in a circle.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 30 cakes, depending on size.
(Can cut recipe in half.)

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Set ice cream out to soften 10 to 15 minutes.
Crush 10 to 15 cookies and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush 10 to 15 more cookie and set aside for topping.
Crumble the remainder of the cookies and mix into the ice cream, Cool Whip and nuts.
Stir to mix all ingredients well.
Place the mixture in the 9 x 13-inch pan over the cookie crust.
Top with the reserved crushed cookies and store in freezer.

title: no-fry doughnuts
directions: In large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, yeast, nutmeg and cinnamon. To the cooled milk, add sugar, salt and melted shortening.
Add this to the flour-yeast mixture.
Beat 1/2 minute.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth. Cover.
Let rise until doubled (50 to 60 minutes).

title: slaw
directions: Place cabbage and onion in bowl and pour sugar over them. Bring all other ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage. Cover and refrigerate.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch together until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onions and pepper.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat just until blended.
Pour into well greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Contains 86 calories per serving.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Cook pie filling as directed. While pie filling is cooking, add the cream cheese.
Place ladyfingers on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
If pie filling and cream cheese are lumpy, use electric mixer to smooth out.
Pour mixture over ladyfingers. Cool 40 minutes. Spread Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: caviar appetizer
directions: Arrange each of these side by side, filling a dinner-size plate.
Serve with water table crackers.
Leave several butter-size knives on the plate so guests can spoon a little of each onto a cracker.
You'll predominately want to spread your cracker with sour cream first, then the eggs and onion, topping off with some caviar and a few capers, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: bacon macaroni salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Add additional mayonnaise before serving, if desired.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix and cook first 6 ingredients until thick, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add gelatine.
Cool, then fold the following into the pumpkin mixture:
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar.
Pour on top of baked crust and let set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freezes well.

title: apple bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, water and oil.
Add applesauce, then remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour batter into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 medium loaves.

title: caramel pecan logs
directions: Prepare fondant according to recipe directions. Let stand (ripen) at room temperature for 24 hours. Divide ripened fondant into fourths. Shape each piece into a 3-inch long log. In a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine caramels, margarine and milk. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until caramels are melted.

title: frozen margarita pie
directions: Chill a medium bowl and beaters from an electric mixer in the freezer.

title: hunan style lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 inch slices.
In a medium bowl beat all the ingredients except Lemon Sauce and lemon slices with a hand beater until smooth.
In a frying pan heat oil (about 1 1/2 inch). Dip chicken pieces one at a time into the batter and fry about 4 pieces at a time until golden brown, turning once.
Drain chicken pieces on paper towel and keep them warm.
Pour Lemon Sauce over chicken pieces and serve.

title: porcupine meat balls and chili sauce
directions: To
make
sauce, combine the chili powder, garlic salt, syrup, oregano
and
tomato
juice
in pot.
In bowl, combine ground beef, raw rice and rest of the ingredients.
Blend well and roll into balls; place in sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Wipe meat with cold cloth.
Place in a large covered skillet. Cover top of chops with lemon, onion and pepper.
Sprinkle with salt.
Dot with margarine and pour tomato juice over top.
Cover and simmer on top of stove for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Add butter, Velveeta and egg. Mix well and pour in casserole. Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: six can casserole
directions: Mix and bake for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Use an 8-inch square pan.
Place fruit; sprinkle lemon juice and sugar on fruit.
Combine flour, oats, cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Cut in butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until fruit is tender when pierced.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until completely moistened. Grease muffin tins.
Fill half to 2/3's with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: crawfish boil
directions: Fill a big kettle with 1/3 water; boil water with seasoners. Add potatoes and bring to boil.
Add corn and bring to boil. Throw in live crawfish and sausage.
Boil 5 to 15 minutes until fish are pink.
Dump it all out on a feed sack and dig in.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Break cake into pieces.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, Pet milk and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix strawberry glaze and strawberries.
Pour over top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: ham, potatoes, cheese in crock-pot
directions: In your crock-pot, layer 2/3 of potatoes, salt and pepper to taste, 1/2 of ham and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat with 1/3 potatoes, etc.
Try to keep most of the potatoes near the bottom since they have to cook through.
Top with soup.
Cook on low for 8 hours or high for 5 to 6 hours.
I serve with green vegetable and some type of bread or roll.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the ground beef (as if you're cooking it for spaghetti). Stir-fry the steak with the onions and boil the noodles.
Get a baking packing pot (pan), something with a deep dish.

title: mommy's potato salad
directions: Peel the potatoes, cut in cubes and cook until tender.
Drain. Add butter while potatoes are still hot. With potato masher, mash the potatoes until smooth, adding the milk until thickness desired.
Add salt, prepared mustard, pickle juice and onion; mix well.
Line a platter with the lettuce leaves. Spoon potato salad on the leaves. Shape into a rounded loaf.
Cut sweet pickles in half lengthwise.
Slice hard-boiled eggs. Arrange the pickle slices and eggs on top of the salad.

title: stir-fried broccoli and carrots
directions: Heat oil in wok or 12-inch skillet until hot.
Add ginger root and garlic.
Stir-fry until light brown for 1 minute.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and salt.
Cover and cook until carrots are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 seconds.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms and oyster sauce.
Cook and stir 30 seconds.
Yields 4 servings.

title: greatest casserole ever
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions for 2 cups cooked rice.
Layer all ingredients
in greased casserole in order given.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: otis campbell's homemade vegetable soup
directions: Usually I boil skinned chicken pieces for about 2 hours to obtain the broth.
I add the listed items and other vegetable leftovers like green beans and corn if they are available.
Bring the broth to a boil and then simmer for about 1 hour.
The soup lasts well in the refrigerator for up to a week and can be frozen. Serves 6 to 8.

title: ellen's ham sandwiches
directions: Mix margarine, poppy seed, mustard, onion and Worcestershire sauce.

title: ladies guild punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix the lemon sherbet, club soda and lemon juice; blend thoroughly.
Add the frozen strawberries.
Add ice cubes and serve.

title: vegetable spread
directions: In food processor, chop together carrots, red pepper, celery and walnuts to coarse consistency. Add ginger, lemon rind and enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together. Chill before serving. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sesame chicken(stir-fried)
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in bowl and stir.
Let marinate 15 minutes.
Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add peas, garlic and chili paste and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add chicken with marinade and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add bamboo shoots and water chestnuts and stir-fry until chicken is almost cooked through, almost 2 minutes.
Mix in broth.
Add sesame seed and green onions.
Stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add sesame oil and toss to coat.
Serve with rice.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Mix together potatoes, onion, celery, water and bouillon. Bring to boil and cook 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until ready to eat, stirring occasionally.

title: baking soda biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll out; cut and bake at 450°.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften the two cheeses at room temperature.
Mix and pat 1/4-inch thick on foil lined cookie sheet.
Soften the cream cheese. Add vegetables and seasonings.
Spread over Velveeta cheese mixture.
Roll into jelly roll log.
Use foil to roll. Makes 2. Freezes well.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in 8-inch square pan 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.
Set pan in pan of cold water for finer texture.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix sugars and margarine together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° or until crust is brown and pie is firm.

title: grandma's enchiladas
directions: Fry onions and ground beef together.
Add cheese, onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Add oregano, comino seed and chili powder to taste.
When done, spoon into center of tortilla and wrap.

title: waldorf salad a la eunice(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Core and dice apples (do not peel).
In a large bowl, sprinkle cut up apples with 1 tablespoon of lemon juice to flavor and keep from discoloring.
Add celery, pineapple and walnuts.

title: date squares
directions: Mix all together and use half for the bottom of the pan.
Pat down firm and then spread the filling and use the remaining mixture on top.
Bake in moderate oven and cut before cool.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and mix until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and cherries (strawberries may also be added).
Chill in refrigerator until thick but not completely set.
Fold in 2 pints Cool Whip. Pour over angel food cake that has been broken into walnut sized pieces with all brown removed.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a large loaf or tube pan.
Chill for at least 6 hours.
Unmold and frost with remaining Cool Whip and garnish with coconut.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator or can be frozen.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Add dried beef and stir occasionally until lightly browned.
Add flour.
Stir until dried beef is well coated with flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over toast or boiled potatoes.

title: maureen's favorite chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl first 6 ingredients.
Bring next 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add hot mixture to large bowl.
Pour into a 12 x 18-inch pan (jelly roll).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes. While warm frost.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with hand mixer.
Put into freezer for 30 minutes or until firm.
Roll in toasted almonds.

title: easy pickled peaches
directions: Put 1 whole clove in center of each peach half.
To liquid from peaches, add other ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over peaches.
Cool and then refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients except nuts.
Put nuts in unbaked shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cocktail mix
directions: Mix together, cover and bake one hour at 225°.
Uncover and bake for another hour.

title: rum balls
directions: Roll wafer crumbs fine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into firm balls.
Roll in 10x sugar and store tightly covered at least 1 week before eating.

title: scrumptious pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix in flour and pecans.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; cool.
Mix 2 cups of Cool Whip with cream cheese and 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of flour mixture that has cooled.
Mix both boxes of pudding with 3 cups milk.
Mix with whip.
Pour on top of Cool Whip mixture; cool until set.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top of pudding layer.
Sprinkle with chocolate and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dream chocolate cake
directions: Sift and set aside flour and sugar.
Bring margarine, water and cocoa to rapid boil.
Pour boiled mixture over mixed flour and sugar.
Then add rest of ingredients.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add 1 beaten egg and mix well. Coat cut up rhubarb with flour and egg mixture.
Turn into bottom crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: best cracker jacks
directions: Boil syrup, butter and cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
Quickly stir in soda.
Add peanuts to popcorn.
Pour syrup over corn.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread on 2 lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in slow oven at 200° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Take out and cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs,
one
at
a time, and beat well after each one.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk and extract.
Mix well. Add coconut.
Mix well.
Use 10-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hamwiches
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Add flour and mix well (soft dough).
Let rise until double in bulk. Divide dough in half.
Roll out into circle 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into pie shapes.
Lay slice of boiled ham on each and roll (looks like crescent rolls).
Brush with egg wash and sprinkle with poppy seed or sesame seed.
Rise again until finger poked in roll leaves indent.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
These freeze well.
They taste best warmed before serving.
This recipe can be doubled, tripled, etc.

title: three cheese and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add combined milk, 1 slightly beaten egg and onion; mix well.
Pour into prepared pie plate, spreading evenly.
Bake 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 4 eggs, broccoli and cheeses; spoon evenly over cornmeal base.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dutch pancakes
directions: Melt butter in an ovenproof skillet; swirl to coat sides. Combine eggs, flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Pour into pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for an additional 40 to 45 minutes.
Good served with syrup or heat a can of Wilderness apple pie filling and serve with that.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add next four ingredients in order.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add everything together except nuts and raisins. Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins last.
Bake at 350° in greased two loaf pans for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: scones(a treat for any time.)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Using pastry blender, mix butter into mixture until mixture looks like fine bread crumbs.
Stir sugar and currants into mixture.
Add milk and mix until it becomes dough-like. Place dough in center of cookie sheet.
Spread out to form a 1-inch thick circle, using your hands.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with butter.

title: easy herbed onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, saute the onion in the butter for 5 to 7 minutes until tender. Meanwhile, combine all remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Add onions, mixing just until blended. Spoon into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes until golden.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and pumpkin pie spice; set aside. Beat egg yolks and vanilla with electric mixer on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar, beating until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in 1/2 cup pumpkin.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold yolk mixture into beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle flour mixture over egg mixture; fold in gently just until combined.
Spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Turn cake out onto towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll up towel and cake, jelly roll style.
Cool.
Unroll cake; spread with Cream Cheese Frosting. Roll up cake.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion; drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours on low.

title: ravioli with 6 cheese italian
directions: Bring 6 cups water to boil.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine or butter to prevent sticking.
Lower to slow boil.
Add ravioli. Slowly boil for 20 to 25 minutes or until desired tenderness. Drain.
Layer 1/2 of the ravioli on bottom of casserole dish. Cover ravioli with Ragu sauce (1/3 jar).
Evenly sprinkle 6 cheese over sauce (1/3 bag).
Layer remaining ravioli, sauce (1/3 jar) and the remaining package of 6 cheese sprinkled evenly.
Cover casserole dish and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli and set some buds aside for garnish.
Saute broccoli, onion and green pepper in butter.
Add soup stock.
Add bay leaf, parsley, thyme and peppercorns.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: potato goodies
directions: Thaw the potatoes for 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sourdough pizza crust
directions: Mix Sourdough, butter and salt.
Work in enough flour to make a dough that can be rolled in a thin layer.
Put it on an oiled baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 500° oven for about 5 minutes. Spread baked dough with your favorite pizza sauce and trimmings. Bake at 425° until sauce bubbles, about 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
In a large bowl mix all above ingredients thoroughly.
Form into loaf and center in a 9x13 pan (it is important to leave room on all four sides of loaf for fat to drain off).
Bake on center rack for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and top meat loaf with a thin layer of ketchup.
Return to oven and continue to bake for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: arkansas shrimp
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small, bite-size pieces.
Mix with salt, Season-All and pepper.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Add oil and cornstarch.
Let set 15 minutes.
Add 2 egg whites, paprika and other seasonings that you might like.
Let set 15 minutes. Stir-fry in a small amount of oil.
Good with soy sauce and stir-fry veggies!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Stir in zucchini.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 5 x 7-inch loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: appetizer quiche
directions: Cut pie crust into approximately 3-inch round circles.
Press into bottom and partially up sides of muffin pans.
Combine beaten eggs and milk; whisk until completely blended.
Add onion, bacon, Swiss cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into muffin tins, 1/2 to 3/4 full; bake at 350° until set.
Serve warm.

title: apricot nut jam
directions: Wash and pit apricots; grind or chop and put into pan with lemon juice.
Add Pectin and gelatin and cook over high, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and bring to full rolling boil, stirring. Boil exactly 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir and skim foam several times for 5 minutes, cooling slightly to prevent floating fruit.
Add nuts.
Fill jars to 1/8 inch of top and place hot, boiled lids atop.
Screw rims on tightly.
Makes about 15 (6 oz.) jars.
DO NOT double recipe.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage and boil water.
Drain well.
Mix eggs, butter, milk and salt.
Add to cabbage and mix well.
Place in greased baking dish; sprinkle with crushed cereal, either Wheaties or corn flakes.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: apricot nut squares
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup of sugar, beat until light.
Stir in lemon rind.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking soda, and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and blend.
Spread on greased 12 x 8 inch pan.

title: summer casserole
directions: Put all vegetables in casserole.
Add water, margarine, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender. Uncover and add cheese.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar.
Heat to dissolve sugar.
Add oil. Pour over combined vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Blend in vanilla and water, then flour.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 300° for 20 minutes or until delicately brown.
Cool, thoroughly and thin.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: oyster pie
directions: Put
layer
of
saltine
crackers and layer of oysters. Beat 2 eggs;
add
milk,
salt, water, pepper, mushroom soup, Tabasco and
Worcestershire
sauce.
Pour
on
top of layered oysters and crackers.
Dab
butter all over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly and light brown.

title: wonton wrapper appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a miniature muffin pan with cooking spray.
Insert wonton wrappers into the muffin pan so as to form small cups.
Bake 5 minutes.
Allow the baked wrappers to cool.
Remove from the pan.

title: tomato bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in 2-quart casserole. Stir in tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper. Sprinkle on top with Parmesan cheese. Place butter on top and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: cider-baked turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place breast, skin side up, in roaster. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Lower oven to 325°.
Combine 1 1/2 cups cider and soy sauce.
Pour over turkey breast.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting frequently, with the cider mixture.

title: taco salad
directions: In 8 x 10-inch baking dish, spread soup out.
Add layer of lettuce, peppers, onions, tomatoes, layer of Fritos and layer of cheese.
Bake just long enough to melt cheese at 375°, approximately 15 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Blend flour into 2 tablespoons melted butter in saucepan. Cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Stir in milk gradually. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt, pepper and cheese until cheese is melted.
Saute ham in 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add eggs.
Cook over medium heat until eggs are set, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese sauce. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of bread crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Chill, covered, overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Sift together flour, brown sugar, nuts and butter.
Spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reserve 1/3 of the crumb mixture (leave in pan).
Combine whites of egg, white sugar, berries and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed to stiff peaks, about 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: almond filled braid
directions: Swedish Dough:
Stir yeast into warm water to dissolve.
Mix well with cream, evaporated milk and egg yolks.
In a large bowl, stir flour, salt and sugar.
Put in margarine.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Spread dough lightly with margarine.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight or up to 4 days.

title: potluck beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, mix together well and simmer about an hour. Serve warm.

title: sausage balls(also known as sausage cookies)
directions: Mix in paper sack.
Roll into balls.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sirnaya paskha(cheese cake)
directions: Put cheese through a fine food chopper or sieve at least 2 times and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until almost white. Add egg yolks and continue creaming.
Add vanilla.
When this mixture is thoroughly blended, add the cheese and mix well.
Add the whipped cream.
Additions of almonds and fruit is optional and added last.
Put the mixture in a cheesecloth lined clay flowerpot, colander or paskha mold.
Put a heavy weight on the top to help press out the excess moisture.
Put container on wire rack so that the cheese will not sit in the drained liquid.
Let drain at least 24 hours.
Chill thoroughly.
This freezes beautifully.
Unmold and remove cheesecloth before serving.
Decorate with bits of candied fruit.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs and beat. Add flour, baking soda and baking powder and beat.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: napoleons
directions: Thaw pastry sheets 20 minutes; unfold gently and roll on floured surface to 18 x 11-inches.
Cut crosswise to make 6 rectangles, about 3 x 11-inches each.
Prick each sheet thoroughly with a fork and bake on ungreased baking sheet in a preheated 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple ham
directions: Score fat on ham; place whole clove in each diamond.
Place ham, fat side up, on a rack in a roasting pan.
Bake in a slow 300° oven.
Allow 20 minutes to the pound.
Baste often with the honey, brown sugar and pineapple mixture.
Remove from oven to meat platter.

title: preacher's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef. Pour off fat. Add all other ingredients. Cook until tender. Serve over toast, optional.

title: beer muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in salt, shortening and 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour (first with spoon, then continue by hand) to make dough easy to handle.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Combine ingredients.
Boil together for 10 minutes, then serve with tortilla chips.

title: black sweet cherry and peach molded salad
directions: Combine gelatin and lemon juice and heat over hot water until dissolved.
Combine with sugar, salt, orange juice and ginger ale. Chill until syrupy and fold in fruits and nuts.
Pour into a ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.
Fill center with cottage cheese.
Garnish with whole cherries with stems. Serves 6 or 8.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then into bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken sweet and sour
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Place chicken parts close together in pan and cover with the mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work sausage and cheese together thoroughly with hands. Gradually work in Bisquick.
Pinch off and roll in small balls. Bake in an ungreased pan at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sliced baked tomatoes(low carb)
directions: Arrange sliced tomatoes on a baking sheet. Put about a teaspoon of mayonnaise on each slice. Sprinkle a little basil, chives, parsley, salt and pepper on each slice. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 300° until the cheese melts.

title: mexican rice
directions: Chop pepper very fine and salt and pepper to taste.
Brown bacon until crisp in skillet.
Remove bacon.
Add chopped onion, pepper and rice.
Brown in bacon grease until onion is soft.
Add tomato sauce plus 1 1/3 sauce cans of water and spices.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until all liquid is absorbed.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Remove grease.
Cook noodles.
Mix meat sauce, pepperoni and cheese; then add in noodles.
Put in a baking dish. Cover.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mixed barbecue beef and pork
directions: Put in Dutch oven and bake at 350° for about 3 hours.
Mash and serve on hamburger buns.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake; cut into 4 equal slices.
Crumble 1/4 in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 can blueberries.
Spread 1/2 bowl Cool Whip over blueberries.
Add 1/4 cake.
Add 1/2 can cherries.
Add 1/2 bowl Cool Whip.
Add 1/4 cake.
Add 1/2 can pineapple.
Add 1/2 bowl Cool Whip.
Add 1/4 cake.
Add rest of blueberries, cherries and pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with bananas, coconut and nuts.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add all other ingredients except flour.
Then add flour in two parts.
Knead until smooth and rubbery.
Place in a tightly covered bowl for 24 hours.
Keep in refrigerator.
Grease top of dough and take off only what you need.
Squeeze rolls and let rise 2 hours before baking.
Replace remainder of dough in refrigerator.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening until crumbly.
Beat egg, add water, salt, sugar, and vinegar.
Add this to flour mixture.
Mix well and roll pie crust.
Bake at 400 degrees for 8-10 minutes.
Makes two 8 inch crusts.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare layers:
mushrooms and onions, shredded Swiss cheese and French bread.
Mix soup, milk and soy sauce.
Pour over all. Make a day ahead and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: swedish cheese potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes into 1 inch wedges.
Arrange in a single layer in a 9 x 12-inch shallow baking pan.
Pour butter over potatoes. Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir until blended.
Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add onion.
Before onion is brown, add broccoli, then stir.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz, rice, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pear cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla, baking soda and water.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in pears.
Dough will be very stiff.
If desired, add raisins and pecans.
Spread in pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast with warm water.
Add cake mix and flour.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out and spread with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Drizzle with powdered sugar.
Frost when cooled for 10 minutes.

title: the best wild rice casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over wild rice and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain and add mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and drained mushrooms.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup boiling water with 1 crumbled bay leaf.
Season with celery salt, garlic salt, pepper, onion salt and paprika.

title: brisket
directions: Trim excess fat off brisket.
Place brisket in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Then cook on low for at least 3 hours.
When you can smell it, you can eat it.

title: baked corn
directions: Add milk to the sugar and cornstarch.
Beat the eggs and combine with salt to the mixture.
Thaw corn before adding to the other ingredients.
Add butter, place in a greased baking dish and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until a silver knife comes out clean.

title: ham delights
directions: Melt margarine; add mustard, onion, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Spread on bread top and bottom, add meat and cheese. Wrap in foil and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Roll in balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the fruit; peel and dice apple.
Whip the cream; add to mayonnaise.
Add sugar.
Mix the fruit cocktail and apples.
Top with cream and sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange drained pineapple slices and cherry halves on sugar mixture.
Mix cake according to box directions.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn upside-down on large platter.
May be served with Cool Whip.

title: grandma's date pudding
directions: Boil brown sugar and water 3 minutes; put in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop in syrup.
Bake 30 minutes in moderate oven.
Top with whipped cream.

title: wildcat slush
directions: Use 2 to 2 1/2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water or to taste.

title: microwave beef and peppers(total cooking time:  8 to 9 minutes)
directions: Pour oil in 3-quart microproof casserole or baking dish.
Add beef strips and stir to coat with oil.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on High (Max power) for 4 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Add green peppers and soy sauce; stir.
Cook, covered, on High (Max power) for 4 to 5 minutes or until green peppers are just tender.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with dry stuffing mix.
Put half in baking dish.
Add chicken, soups and water.
Add rest of stuffing on top and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Can use turkey instead of chicken.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and saute in butter until limp.
Pour onions into casserole dish; add cream and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: grandma markle's molasses cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Scald soda and alum together with a little hot water.
Add flour, enough to thicken, about 3 1/2 cups.
Brush top with egg, which has been beaten.
Bake at 350°.

title: lite pie
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into yogurt.
Add thawed Cool Whip and blend. Pour into crust.
Let set in refrigerator for about 4 hours.

title: tracy turtles
directions: In small saucepan heat butter and evaporated milk until butter is melted.
In separate 2-quart saucepan cook sugar, corn syrup and salt over medium heat until it reaches the firm ball stage (245°) on candy thermometer.
Slowly stir in hot milk mixture so that sugar mixture does not stop boiling.
Stirring constantly, cook mixture until candy reaches firm ball stage again.
Remove pan from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cool caramel to room temperature.

title: hampton crab imperial
directions: Preheat oven to 375° for 10 minutes.
Saute pimiento and green pepper in butter.
Make a heavy cream sauce by melting butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat; stir in flour, milk and salt. Continue stirring until mixture is smooth and thick.
Combine sauteed vegetables, cream sauce and other ingredients except crab, mayonnaise and paprika.
Mix in 3/4 cup mayonnaise.
Fold in crabmeat very gently so lumps will not break up.

title: sugar-free fruit cake
directions: Bring to a boil the dates, prunes, raisins, margarine and water.
Then mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, beaten eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Add to cooled fruit.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Add sugar to slightly beaten egg.
Add juice and oil.
Mix in (sifted) dry ingredients.
Add rind, cranberries and nuts.
Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350° in greased, floured loaf pan.
May put wax paper in bottom of pan to prevent sticking.

title: brenda's pineapple-raspberry cream punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice and ginger ale over ice cream and sherbet and stir until melted and blended.
Makes 2 dozen (4 ounce) servings.
Double all ingredients to serve 50.

title: easy pork b.b.q.
directions: Place in crock pot.
Cook on slow all day.
Stir every so often to break up pork.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown the hamburger and onions together.
Add salsa, cheese and refried beans.
Cook until cheese is melted and it's ready!

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in Bundt cake pan that has been sprayed and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jim's french toast
directions: Place small amount of cooking oil in skillet.
Dip bread in eggnog and fry until done.
Jam, syrup or fruit can be used.
Very good topped with fresh sliced peaches or strawberries and topped with whipped cream.
Um-m-m-m good!

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, milk and well beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with 1/4 cup of cracker crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: grilled cheese with peperoni(kindergarten recipe)
directions: Put butter on bread.
Put cheese and peperoni on bread.
Cook in frying pan until it is like toast.
Serve with chips and peperoni on the side.

title: skinny macaroni salad(lo-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, tomatoes, onions, basil, garlic, vinegar, oil and pepper.
Cover and let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil chicken; cool.
Remove from bones and cut into chunks. Spread broccoli in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chicken over broccoli.
Combine mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Remove seeds from chiles and chop them. In large skillet, heat small amount of oil.
Add chiles and garlic and saute.
Drain and break up tomatoes.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Add tomatoes, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano and reserved tomato liquid to the chiles and garlic.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: chocolate peanut goodies
directions: Combine frosting and peanut butter in large mixing bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add oats and chopped peanuts, stir until thoroughly blended.
Press candy mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan. Cut into 36 pieces.
Decorate tops with peanut halves.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Yields 1 3/4 pounds candy.

title: grilled sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread thick on buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: candied pecan halves
directions: Cook slowly all ingredients except pecans
; stir until soft ball forms in water.
Stir in 2 cups pecans.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Break apart as it cools.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Grate onion and green pepper.
Add seasoned salt.
Add cream cheese and pineapple.
Mix all together and form into a ball.
Can roll in chopped pecans.

title: buttermilk fruit topping
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine buttermilk and pudding mix. Beat on low for 2 minutes; fold in whipped topping. Chill for an hour and serve over fruit.

title: chicken kelly
directions: Coat chicken with egg, then with bread crumbs. Brown in small amount of oil. Line greased 9 x 13 pan with chicken, mushrooms, then cheese. Dissolve bouillon in water; pour over chicken casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Combine corn syrup, flour, 3 eggs, salt, vanilla and sugar; mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Brush pie crust with white of egg.
Pour butter over pie and cover with chopped black walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes in a very slow oven at 250°.

title: healthy wise brownies
directions: In a small saucepan melt margarine; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, water and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cocoa powder and baking powder until well mixed.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spray the bottom only of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with nonstick spray coating.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly.
Remove from pan.
Cut into 16 bars.
Sprinkle with the powdered sugar.
Yields 16 (2-ounce) servings.
Per serving:
101 calories, 1.45 g protein, 14.8 g carbohydrates, 4.1 g total fat, .76 g saturated fat, .5 mg cholesterol and 76 mg sodium.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
