directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; pour into buttered baking dish. Top with remaining ingredients.
Blend coconut, nuts, sugar and flour.
Add the butter and mix.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes. Bake at 375° until lightly brown, about 20 minutes.

title: coconut shrimp
directions: Peel and de-vein shrimp, leaving tails on.
Slit down inner curve of shrimp and press lightly to flatten.
In shallow dish, combine cornstarch, salt, and cayenne pepper.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.

title: simple snow capped pate
directions: Press mixture into a 2-cup mold or small dish. Chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Unmold pate by running a small metal spatula around edge and invert onto a serving plate.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature and mix all together.
Add pecans.
Shape and roll into rolls.
Cover with chili powder. Roll in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut in thin slices to serve.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Put chicken and marinade in a Ziploc bag; let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Grill for 5 minutes on each side.
Baste with marinade after turning.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and garlic in a small pan over low heat or microwave on Low until melted.
In a shallow bowl, mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Brush chicken with butter and roll in crumbs.
Place foil on a cookie sheet and spray with nonstick spray.
Place chicken on pan.
Bake 1 hour; check at 50 minutes.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions, saving the juice.
Combine all ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yield:
4 pints.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix cake by directions and bake in two (8 or 9-inch) round pans.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Direction 1:
Cut biscuits in fourths.
Drop in bundt pan. Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Brown slowly in oil over medium heat.
Remove pieces of chicken when browned.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Cook about 15 minutes, stirring constantly, until a rich brown roux.
Lower heat.
Add onion and celery; cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Gradually stir in water.
Add parsley, bay leaf, thyme, chicken pieces and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Add warm water to mix; pour on warm cake.

title: orange fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale together in a very large freezer-safe container.
Freeze at least 24 hours prior to use. Take out of freezer about 4 hours prior to use and leave at room temperature to thaw slightly.
Place in a large punch bowl and chop.
Add ginger ale.

title: zucchini crab cake
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Add cracker crumbs (2 cups or desired consistency).
Make cakes and fry.

title: parmesan-crusted perch(low-fat)
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon cheese and next 5 ingredients; spread evenly on 1 side of fillets.
Place fillets, coated side up, on a rack coated with cooking spray.
Place rack in broiler pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil 6 inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) for 18 minutes, or until golden and fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: delicious cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs; add juice from oranges and break oranges into pieces.
Add to mixture, stirring with a spoon. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Blend flour with salt and soda in small bowl.
Gradually add sugar to butter in mixing bowl.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually; mix well.
Stir in candy pieces.
Chill dough for easy handling. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, butter, salt and evaporated milk for 6 minutes in a heavy saucepan.
Place the chocolate chips, German chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts in a bowl.
Pour the boiling syrup over the ingredients.
Beat until chocolate is all melted (about 4 minutes).
Pour into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: party punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place container in freezer.
Punch must have 2 hours to thaw before serving.
Once the punch has thawed for 2 hours, pour into punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over it.

title: almond punch
directions: Mix in a gallon jar first 4 ingredients.
Finish filling the jar with water.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Best when made the day before.

title: barbecue beans(home economics)
directions: You will also need cupcake papers.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add crushed pineapple (drained), frozen strawberries in syrup, mashed bananas and walnuts.
Then put 1/2 of this mixture in a pan and put in the refrigerator until jello is firm.
Once this is firm put sour cream over mixture and put remaining jello mixture over the sour cream.
Chill.
Serves 18.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and dressing mix well and form ball or log.
Chill. Roll in nuts and chill.
Serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Place in 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Dilute soup with 1 soup can of water. Pour over chicken.
Top with onion soup mix.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg yolk until smooth.
Sift flour and salt together.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until very light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
(Note:
The crust will be soft.)
Immediately place pieces of chocolate evenly over crust; when it becomes
soft, spread it evenly over top.
Sprinkle the nuts on top.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: zucchini bread(two loaves)
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll in crushed pecans and refrigerate overnight.

title: czarnina (soup)
directions: Put duck, salt, onion, vinegar and tomato juice in a large pot.
Add enough water to make about 2 gallons.
Boil all this until duck is tender.
Remove duck and onion.

title: beef soup
directions: First, chop all vegetables.
Brown beef cubes in hot oil. Stir in leeks. Cover and cook on low heat about 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley. Cover and simmer for 50 to 60 minutes. Add parsley. Add more hot water, if needed.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Empty cake mix into large bowl.
Beat egg and add to mix.
Add Cool Whip (will be very stiff).
Stir together; do not mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoons into confectioners sugar.
Roll into cookies and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will still be gummy when you take them out of oven.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Melt
margarine.
Chopped chicken should be spread in a large casserole.	Spread	can
of mushroom soup over chicken, then spread
dressing over soup.
Add cup of stock with butter and spread over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato omelette
directions: Beat the eggs thoroughly and stir in the parsley.
Cut potatoes into small pieces and add to eggs.
Melt the butter in a skillet and when just beginning to smoke faintly, pour in the omelette mixture.
Cook over a moderate heat, until golden brown. Fold over and serve on a very hot plate.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Blend well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chili hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan; cook until thickened.
Place in jars and seal.

title: 6 weeks orange muffins
directions: Put everything but the eggs into a large bowl and mix together.
Fold the beaten eggs in last.
Put in a covered bowl and store in icebox.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap chicken pieces with bacon.
Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over all.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: quick fantastic focaccia bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pat out dough onto a greased cookie sheet.
Spread pressed garlic onto dough.
Sprinkle Romano cheese over crust, then Mozzarella cheese and oregano.
Arrange sliced thin tomatoes and sliced roasted peppers.
Sprinkle additional Romano cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serve hot.

title: "bac n spinach" quiche
directions: Line a pie pan with pastry crust. Sprinkle crumbled bacon. Sprinkle spinach. Sprinkle cheese. Mix eggs and half and half well. Pour over quiche. Sprinkle salt and pepper. Dot with butter. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Continue baking at 350° for approximately 40 minutes. When knife comes out clean, it is done. Let stand for 15 minutes. Serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Grease pan or spray with Pam.

title: crustless ham broccoli pie
directions: Mix 2 cups cheese, ham, onion and broccoli and put in 2 pie plates sprayed with Pam.
Beat remaining ingredients, except cheese, with wire whisk about 1 minute.
Pour over other mixture. Bake at 375° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes. Top with rest of cheese.
Bake about 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown beef and onions. Stir in tomatoes, beans, corn, tomato sauce, water, mushrooms, taco seasoning and chili powder. Bring to a boil and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: my special meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Put into a Pam sprayed casserole dish (deep).

title: apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples.
Mix with fork.
Add sugar, nuts, oil, cinnamon and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda, add to apples. Pour into 9 x 12-inch glass pan, bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy layered cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham crackers over butter.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and coconut.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk all over the top.
Bake around 20 minutes at 350°, until golden brown.
Cool a little and cut in bars.

title: mushroom parmesan
directions: Toss mushrooms with half the oil in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine the dry ingredients and sprinkle over mushrooms. Pour the remaining oil over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lentil patties
directions: Mix well and form into patties.
Fill a 1/4 measuring cup with mixture to use as a mold and then flatten slightly.
Place patties on a baking tray and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with a gravy.

title: pan pizza
directions: Slice dough.
Lay side by side on pizza pan.
This will make one large cookie.
Bake as directed on package.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Add egg, beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamy mixture at low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing from pan.
Yields approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: four-bean bake
directions: Drain first three kinds of beans.
Add pork and beans, blending well.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel. Lightly brown the onion in a small amount of the bacon fat.
Mix vinegar and brown sugar.
Add the onion and simmer for 15 minutes. Add this sauce and the crisp bacon to the beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour, stirring twice as it bakes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat 3 eggs.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup sugar; mix well.
Add pineapple.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cut 4 slices bread into cubes and put on top of pineapple mixture.
Melt butter and pour over bread cubes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (cover it half of the time).

title: spiced fruit slush
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add tea bags and remove from heat.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Remove and discard tea bags.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.

title: baked stream side trout
directions: Clean
the
fish,
roll
in
cornmeal or cracker crumbs (Ritz crackers tend to be sweeter than saltines) and wrap with a slice of	bacon.	Seal
in
foil	and
cook for 15 minutes, turning frequently.

title: swiss canape broils
directions: Mix together and spread on bread or crackers (party rye or small breads).
Broil 3 inches from heat until cheese melts. Yield: 2 cups.

title: braised sirloin tips(low calorie)
directions: Place a large, nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle pepper and meat tenderizer on meat.
Brown meat on all sides, turning often, until well browned.
Add garlic and onions and cook until onions are translucent.
Add broth, wine and soy sauce and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shell and cheese. In bottom of pie shell, put
1 1/2 cups cheese, then pour jalapeno mixture over it. Top with another 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: just my size pizza
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Unroll pizza dough.
Pinch off some and make a round circle.
Flatten with your palm.
On a sprayed cookie sheet, spoon pizza sauce over top with toppings.
Bake for about 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Chill evaporated milk 24 hours.
Mix lemon Jell-O with 1 cup of boiling water and chill until consistency of egg whites.
Combine finely crushed graham crackers, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Mix well and line pan to form crust, taking out 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Cream the cream cheese with 1 cup sugar. Beat milk until thick.
Add cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add Jell-O mixture and dash of salt.
Beat well and pour into crust.
Sprinkle top with the cup of graham crackers removed. Chill in refrigerator.

title: spiced apple dump cake
directions: Put the apple pie filling in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add water.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit and pour butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise.
If not serving immediately, wait until serving before adding onions and bacon for best results.

title: pecan patties
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cook in heavy pan.
Bring to boil, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Put pan in cold water; beat and drop on wax paper.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: taco dip
directions: (All cheese can be low-fat.)
Mix the sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning with mixer.
Spread in pan.
Pour taco sauce over cheese mixture.
Chop tomatoes; spread over sauce.
Top with cheese.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Thinly slice zucchini; add to oil with onion, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and rosemary.
Saute over medium heat until zucchini is tender.
Toss in tomatoes and continue to saute for 5 more minutes.
Turn into a serving dish; sprinkle with cheese.

title: shrimp louie
directions: Bake or fry shrimp.
Let cool and remove tails.
Lay shrimp in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch lasagna dish.
Cover with mushrooms, sauce and cheese. Continue to layer until pan is full. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve alone or with noodles or your favorite
pasta.

title: mushroom-beef-barley soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer for 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Serves 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1-quart saucepan, scald milk.
Add butter.
In 1 1/2-quart
casserole, beat eggs slightly; stir in milk, corn with liquid, onion and salt.
Set casserole in shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water in pan around casserole 1-inch deep.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Fry chicken and break into pieces.
Put soups, chicken, vegetables and 1/2 cup of milk into a 9x13 pan.
Melt butter and mix with 1 cup of milk and flour (will be lumpy).
Pour on top of chicken mixture.

title: stir-fried pork tenderloin with vegetables
directions: Cut tenderloin diagonally into 1/8-inch thick slices.
In medium bowl, mix pork with next 5 ingredients.
In 12-inch skillet over high heat, in 3 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook broccoli, mushrooms, carrot and salt, stirring quickly and frequently until vegetables are coated with oil.
Add water and stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Spoon vegetables onto warm platter; keep warm.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer in Pyrex dish in the order listed and chill.
Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Line 10 x 14-inch cookie sheet with wax paper.
Spread mixture over wax paper and sprinkle nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
roll up in wax paper, then in tea towel until cool.

title: how to make your own brown sugar
directions: Mix well and let set overnight so the molasses absorbs well into sugar, then store in airtight container to stay moist.

title: potato pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in a pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: baked stuffed morels(great michigan recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut stems from morels.
Arrange caps, stem side up, in buttered baking dish.
Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
Saute leeks or onion in fat.
Remove with slotted spoon.

title: skillet chicken with rice
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Saute in hot oil until lightly brown.
Remove.
Drain beans (save the juice) and add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir liquid mixture, rice, soup, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 bay leaf and 1 cup of water into pan.
Bring to a boil.
Return chicken to pan; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Stir occasionally.
Discard bay leaf; stir in beans.
Heat thoroughly.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and carrots until crisp and tender.
Set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together
and pour into greased, 2 quart casserole. Top with
Ritz
crackers,
crumbled
and mixed with 1/2 stick margarine (melt
margarine
and
add to cracker crumbs). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian bean soup
directions: Drain and rinse beans. Then put into a medium pot and cover with cold water by 2-inches. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until just tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Drain and set aside.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Place broken pretzels on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and drizzle over pretzels.
Sprinkle buttered pretzels with granulated sugar.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
While cooling, stir frequently to keep pretzels loose.

title: date roll
directions: Cut the cherries in pieces.
Mix everything together.
Put in the cherry juice and make good and moist.
It will take a while to mix it together, then separate into 2 rolls and work in 1 cup graham cracker crumbs into each roll.

title: layered strawberry-cracker dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Meanwhile, slice berries, reserving a few whole berries for garnish.
Sprinkle sliced berries with sugar.
Fold whipped topping into Jell-O.
Blend well.
Fold in sliced berries.

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand 30 minutes.
Add undrained pineapple; mix and cook 30 minutes (I cook about 20 minutes). Remove from heat.
Add gelatin; mix.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: great potato dish
directions: Mix all and put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Slice corn kernels by cutting 1/2 way through and then scraping the rest for the milk.
Fry the bacon crisp and set aside.
Fry the ham or sausage slices in the bacon drippings.
Add corn and cook until done.
Add milk.
Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat together
all
ingredients with electric beater at least 3 minutes until
well mixed.
Heat cooking oil in a deep fryer or skillet until
very
hot.
Put
batter into a funnel. Be sure to cover
spout
with	finger.
Then, holding over hot oil, release some of
the
batter
in
a circular motion, then crisscross to form one funnel cake.
Cook until light brown on both sides. Drain
on
paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.
Extreme caution as oil is very hot.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, then gradually add sugar to mixture, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix after each addition. Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Spoon hot glaze over warm cake.
Let cool completely.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add all ingredients together.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250° in tube pan (floured and greased; do not use Pam).

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in pan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook, medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until no syrup left in pan.
Pour and spread on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine.
Sift together flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture.
Add the egg. Add nuts and oatmeal. Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet. Press down with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken veg-stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
Coat skillet with vegetable spray and allow to heat to 325° for 1 to 2 minutes. Add chicken and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove chicken from skillet and reserve soy sauce; set aside.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid; set aside.
Add green peppers and onion to skillet and fry 4 minutes until tender-crisp. Return chicken.
Add chestnuts and mushrooms.

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: Combine flour and baking powder; stir well. Add milk, eggs and butter. Stir until smooth. Add bacon and sweet potato, stirring well.
Heat 3 to 4-inches of oil to 375° in a Dutch oven. Carefully drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry 2 minutes or until fritters are golden brown. Drain well on paper towels. Serve warm with maple syrup.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Line bottom of greased ovenproof casserole with raisins.
Cut bread in 1-inch strips; dip each in melted butter and arrange a layer over raisins.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over bread.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake in 375° oven until bread is browned and a knife blade inserted in center of pudding comes out clean.
Serve plain or with whipped cream. Serves 6.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, molasses and egg into oil; set aside.
Then sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice.
Add molasses mixture to flour mixture and blend.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into 1 inch balls, or larger if preferred.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Cook until mixture forms a firm ball when dropped into water. In small second boiler, cook 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Cook slowly, a little longer than the first cooking.
Do not let it crystallize.
Add first cooking to beaten egg whites and beat.
Add the second cooking and beat and beat.
Fold in all the nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined trays.

title: swiss chocolate mousse
directions: Whip heavy cream until it stands in a peak.
Refrigerate. Combine two eggs, three egg yolks and sugar in a stainless bowl and whisk till the mixture stands to a peak.
Melt chocolate over a double boiler (not warmer than body temperature).
Blend all the egg/sugar mixture with the melted chocolate a little at a time. Fold in whipped cream, reserving four spoonfuls for garnish.
Add chopped nuts or chocolate chips, if you desire.
Fill in serving dishes and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and molasses and beat together for one minute.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven of 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or a nondairy topping.

title: hamburger sour cream casserole
directions: You will need 2-quart casserole dish.

title: honey balls
directions: Put everything in a big bowl.
Mix it with your hands if your mom will let you or with a spoon.
Make it into little balls, small size.
Put the balls on a cookie sheet.
You can eat them whenever you want.
Don't cook them.

title: peanut butter soup
directions: Clean and trim the meat of fat.
Cut into pieces as desired. Boil the meat with 2 cups of water.
Chop shallots, onions and salt.
Boil the meat until it is half cooked.
Mix peanut butter with 2 cups of water, made into a smooth paste and add pepper and tomato sauce, also dry spices desired.
Add the rest of the water. Continue to boil until the meat is tender and peanut butter oil comes to the surface of the soup.
Serve with cooked rice, yams or potatoes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Drain.
Beat eggs and cheese.
Add warm drained spaghetti and toss.
In a 10-inch greased pie pan, pour mixture to form a crust.
Set aside.
Saute peppers and onions until tender.
Add sour cream.
Pour into spaghetti crust.
Cook sausage well, breaking it with a spoon.
Drain fat. Add water, tomato paste to sausage and mix well.
Heat to boil and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Pour over pie.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Let set 5 minutes.
Cut into serving portions.

title: oven stew
directions: In roasting pan or Dutch oven, mix meat, carrots, celery, onions, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix flour, sugar and salt. Stir into meat mixture. Add tomatoes and wine.
Cover and bake for 4 hours at 350°.
Check for tenderness.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add squash.
Mix well; blender works well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch pan in order listed.
(Do not mix!)
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: grape wine
directions: Place ingredients in gallon jug.
Slowly fill with warm water, shaking to dissolve sugar. Fill until water reaches 1-inch from top.
Put large balloon on neck of jug.
Put in a warm area for 3 weeks.
Put in bottles and store.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, cocoa, milk and salt.
Cook until soft ball forms when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, cool until just a little hotter than lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: pear preserves
directions: Combine pears and sugar in heavy pot.
Let set overnight. Bring slowly to boiling, stirring frequently.
Boil gently until fruit becomes clear and syrup is medium thick.
Add lemon juice. Pour while hot into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: stove top barbecued chicken
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet.
Add the onion and cook it, stirring until it is softened.
Stir in the ketchup, water, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add the chicken to the skillet, placing what used to be the skin side down and spoon the sauce over pieces. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover, turn chicken and cook for another 15 minutes or until tender.

title: sunday morning casserole
directions: Layer bread, cheese and sausage in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together.
Pour over bread layer. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Add milk to can of mushroom soup; blend until smooth.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: wild rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Bring broth, water, celery, onion and rice to a boil.
Cover tightly and cook on low heat until all water is absorbed, 1/2 hour.
Drain mushrooms and add.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook until done. Add 1 heaping tsp. soda. Stir and then pour out on a buttered cookie sheet.

title: cherries on a cloud
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Cover baking sheet with heavy brown paper. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Spoon meringue into desired shape on paper, building upside.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off oven; leave meringue in oven with door closed 1 hour.
Remove from oven; cool.

title: cucumber tuna salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a medium bowl.
Cook on medium heat and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool for 1 minute, then add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave celery and onion with a tablespoon margarine 4 minutes.
Stir in large bowl chopped chicken breast, rice, celery, onions, cream of chicken soup, mayo and chicken broth.
Mix altogether.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Crush corn flakes on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients; shape and put in baking dish. Put cheese on top of loaf.
Mix other items and pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground meat.
Chop onion and tops from bell peppers. Saute with ground beef; drain off fat.
Add cooked rice and drained corn.
Add tomatoes and juice, A.1. sauce, Lea & Perrins sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place remaining mixture in casserole dish.
Set peppers in mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May add cheese last 5 minutes.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; arrange in ovenproof dish.
Layer chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over broccoli and
chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese. Bake until bubbly.

title: meat balls(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Cook on high in crock-pot until done, about 3 hours. Great hors d'oeuvre; will be the hit of a party.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts and shred.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, tomatoes and chili powder.
Crush chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chicken and soup.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can use more grated cheese.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Beat baking mix, margarine, garlic salt and eggs with hand beater until blended.
Stir in zucchini and green onions.
Grease heated griddle to 400°.
For each patty, spoon 1/4 cup mixture onto hot griddle and spread slightly.
Cook patties until dry around edges.
Turn and cook other side until golden brown.
Top each patty with dollop of sour cream, if desired.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil; let it stand till it cools.
Pack cucumbers in quart jars and add one large bunch of dill to each jar.
Fill jars with vinegar mixture.
Seal after 2 or 3 days.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix together pudding, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Stir constantly. (If you want peanut butter filling, add 1/2 cup peanut butter at this point and use vanilla pudding.) Stir in powdered sugar until the consistency of Play Dough.
Shape into eggs.
Place on a cookie sheet and put a toothpick in the center of each one. Freeze at least 2 hours (overnight works best).

title: chicken soup
directions: Put all ingredients into big pot with 4 cups water and cook 3 hours.

title: vietnamese eggroll
directions: Mix turkey, pork, pepper, diced green onion, fish sauce and white onion.
Roll in eggroll skin and deep fry until golden brown.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Dissolve soda in the water and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Also add egg yolks and vanilla.
Last, add the flour.
Don't chill the dough.
Roll out and cut in your favorite design (circles, stars or valentines).

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Let stand 4 hours.

title: sky high meringue
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cold water together and bring to boil on stovetop. Stir and remove when thick
and clear. Cool. Beat

all egg whites until stiff. Add six tablespoons of sugar one tablespoon at a time. Add dash of salt and vanilla. Add cooked mixture and continue to beat for two minutes. Spread on pie shell and bake for fifteen minutes at 350 degrees.

title: onion chicken
directions: Mix both soups together.
Place chicken in casserole dish. Pour soup over chicken. Bake at 350° until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop from teaspoon onto baking sheet. Crisscross with fork. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool on pan before you remove cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together.
Cauliflower and bacon are optional.

title: fudgy chip bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine cookies, flour, coconut and chocolate chips.
Stir in margarine, condensed milk and vanilla extract. Spread into greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or lightly browned around edges.
Cool; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer until tender.
Cool.
Take off bones.
Mix chicken with broth, soup and stuffing mix.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: baked corn and oysters
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Pour mixture into a greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake or oysters will become tough.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until potatoes are soft.
Cover with French fried onions. Bake 10 minutes longer.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: cheese potato puffs
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese and onion; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll in corn flakes.
Bake on greased baking sheet in hot 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: harvest soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and ginger in butter.
Season with spices. Add to pureed squash and carrots.
Heat well, incorporating enough vermouth and chicken stock to give a creamy consistency. Add the half and half.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to hot (400°).
Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups with Pam.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda onto waxed paper.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the dry mixture to add to the berries.

title: silly fruity salad
directions: Cook eggs, juice, sugar and flour until thickens. Chill well. Add whip cream. Mix and pour over fruit and marshmallows.

title: banana berry punch
directions: Mix fruit and juice in blender, then add pop.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix the flour and sugar together well.
Beat the egg and add to the flour and sugar mixture.
Add the vinegar and pineapple juice.
Cook in a small pan on low heat.
Continue stirring until thick.
Cool.
When cool, pour over the apples, pineapple and peanuts.
Add the whipped topping and mix well.
Chill before serving.
May sprinkle chopped nuts on top as a garnish.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli spears and place in bottom of a baking dish. Cook and debone chicken and add on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Crumble crackers and top.
Place a pat of butter on crackers and cook in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie filling as directed on box.
Add dry Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into crust and let cool.

title: sole in parsley sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, over medium heat, dissolve bouillon in 1/2 cup water.
Add carrots and celery.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain vegetables, reserving liquid for sauce.
Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper.
Place 2 tablespoons vegetable mixture in center of each fillet.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.

title: victory cake
directions: Combine raisins, sugar, water, shortening and spices. Heat to boiling and simmer 2 minutes. Cool. Add flour, soda and salt to raisin mixture and mix well. Add walnuts. Bake in a greased 9-inch tube or 9-inch square pan. Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes, just until cake tests done.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Dice everything as small as possible; can use food processor, but don't pulverize it into mush.
Combine and chill.

title: chocolate-mint smoothie
directions: Heat 1/2 cup milk just until hot.
Combine hot milk and cocoa mix in container of an electric blender; process until smooth. Add remaining 1/2 cup milk and flavorings; blend well.
Add ice cream and process until smooth.

title: geneva's strawberry pie filling
directions: Add all ingredients, except strawberries.
Boil until clear and thickened.
Pour over berries in baked pie shell.

title: cheddar scones
directions: Combine 1st four ingredients.
Cut in cold butter until crumbly.
Sir in cheese.
In separate bowl, stir together egg and half and half.
Gradually add to flour mixture stirring with fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 3-4 times, roll into a ball.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a large Dutch oven or casserole.
Add onions; saute over medium heat until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and salt.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring often until cabbage is wilted, about 5 minutes.
Add rice, garlic, cumin and turmeric; saute about 2 minutes.
Stir in broth, more salt, if needed, and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Sprinkle tomatoes on top.
Cover; cook until rice is tender, about 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 main dish servings or 6 to 8 side dish servings.

title: "gone to heaven" potatoes
directions: Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out seed.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine garlic and oil. Mix well.
In small bowl, combine parsley, thyme, marjoram, paprika and Parmesan; mix well.
Cut each loaf crosswise into diagonal slices without cutting all the way through.
Brush cut sides of slices with garlic oil.
Sprinkle herb mixture between slices.
Wrap each loaf in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake until heated through, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Unwrap and serve immediately.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups of warm water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Gradually add sifted flour.
More water may be added for right consistency.
Let rise until double in size, knead down and roll out.
Serves 50.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Thoroughly mix; dampen fingers and form into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Use oil from artichokes to fry scallions.
Mix other ingredients and add to scallions.
Add artichokes.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: veal marsala
directions: Dredge veal in mixture of flour, oregano, salt and pepper. Heat a little oil in a large skillet and saute veal until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms and wine.
Cover and cook for 5 to 10 minutes until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and dressing to taste, then add to salad.
It's better if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Wash chicken.
In oven melt shortening and butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Place skin side down in shortening. Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Turn and cook another 30 minutes until done.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Blend soft oleo, egg, cocoa and salt; beat well (until smooth).
Add milk and vanilla; mix.
Add sugar until spreading consistency.
(May add either more milk or powdered sugar.)

title: weese's wealie's
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Put layer of mixture into paper cups in small tart pans.
Put layer of peanut butter (chunky).
Add top layer of chocolate mixture (thin layers).
Chill well.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Mix 3/4 of coconut in Cool Whip.
Set in icebox while cake is cooking.
Let cake cool.
With fork poke cake all over.
Spread on pineapple with juice, then spread on cream of coconut, then pecans. Then spread Cool Whip on cake.
Sprinkle with rest of coconut. Keep cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, then vanilla. Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours in buttered, floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, green chilies and Cheez Whiz.
Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce and layer.
(Start with chicken mixture.)
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
After baked, you can top with chopped lettuce and tomatoes.

title: layered vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables well. Layer each one evenly in large casserole dish. Dot each layer with a bit of butter. Add salt and pepper to taste. Top with cheese, then spread evenly with undiluted soup to cover vegetables. Sprinkle with paprika. Add onion rings. Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Remove foil and continue baking 15 to 20 minutes until onion rings are lightly browned. Serves 8 to 10.

title: dianne's nachos
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning, chili beans, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread the lettuce. Chop tomatoes.
Add taco mixture onto tortilla chips.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Add cheese.
Place in microwave oven for 10 to 20 seconds just long enough to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, basting occasionally.
Cover after baking.

title: "no bake" chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil in large saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients, stirring well after each.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: tamale bake
directions: Prepare cornmeal mush; pour about half into an 8-cup shallow ovenproof casserole and spread evenly.
Pour remaining into a greased pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, and chill.
Saute onion and green pepper until soft in salad oil in frying pan; add meat, breaking up with a fork.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix, chili powder and tomatoes; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in olives and 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Pour over cornmeal mush in casserole; cover and chill.
About 1 hour before serving, turn out cornmeal mush from pan; divide in half, then each half into thirds.
Cut each piece to make 12 pie-shaped wedges.
Arrange on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place casserole in cold oven.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until bubbly hot.

title: pepperoni pizza(homestyle)
directions: Thaw frozen bread loaf by covering with paper towel until pliable or microwave about 20 minutes at power level 1.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease pizza pan or cookie sheet with shortening. Evenly spread dough on pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over dough. Spread cheese out on top of sauce.
Evenly place pepperoni, onion, mushrooms and any other toppings on cheese.
Place on center shelf; cook for 12 minutes, or until done around edges.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: easy green rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and broccoli together; put in casserole dish and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: granny's squash casserole
directions: Mix; pour into casserole dish.
Top wiht 2/3 cup corn bread crumbs.
Bake until brown, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: spread
directions: Grate cucumbers and let stand for 1 hour and drain.
Add onion, celery, carrots and pepper.
Soften cream cheese and blend all vegetables.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency and salt to taste.

title: pickles for freezer
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and peppers together.
Add salt.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Drain.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, including sugar.
Make a well in dry ingredients; add remaining.
Mix together until smooth. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Then frost with whipped cream and garnish with the pared cherries.

title: braided egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add enough flour to make a heavy batter.
Beat well.
Add salt, oil and all but 2 tablespoons of egg.
Add more flour to make a firm dough.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and allow to double (about 1 1/2 hours). Punch down and knead lightly.
Let double again, about 1 hour. Punch down and divide in half.
Divide each half into thirds and roll into ropes. Braid each half and pinch to seal ends. Brush with remainder of egg. Makes 2 loaves. Bake about 35 minutes at 400°.

title: janet's 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in a casserole dish using 1/2 of the peas. Thaw remaining peas and mix with ranch dressing.
Spread the mixture on top and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Mix well.
Makes 8 gallons.
You may slice oranges and lemon to float on surface.
Serves 100.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, nutmeg, eggs, milk and butter. Mix everything together and pour in a 9-inch unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with remainder of ingredients except potato chips.
Put chicken into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, until bubbly.
Top with crushed potato chips and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake a few more minutes, uncovered.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: black-bean salsa
directions: Up to day ahead, rinse and drain beans.
In bowl combine ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate, covered, until serving. Makes 4 servings (3 cups).

title: enchilada pie
directions: Slice onions and bell peppers.
Mince garlic.
Cook beef until no longer pink.
Remove beef with a slotted spoon.
Add onions, bell peppers, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and cook until soft, about 15 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon and return meat to pan.
Add drained tomatoes, vinegar, cumin, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Break up tomatoes. Simmer 10 minutes.
Grate cheeses.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon lightly.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Add okra, tomatoes and seasoning. Simmer slowly 30 to 45 minutes.
Watch carefully that vegetables do not burn.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions covered in butter for 20 minutes.
Add broth, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Boil.
Sprinkle bread with cheese and broil until light brown.
Ladle soup into bowls and float bread.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Peel and prepare orange sections.
(May use canned Mandarin oranges.)
Drain all fruit well.
Half the cherries.
Combine fruits; add marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in sour cream or yogurt. Mix lightly.
Top with remaining cherries.
Chill 24 hours.

title: butterhorn cookies
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in butter with yeast, yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend into flour mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, add 2 cups sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk. Boil together for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Allow time to become firm.

title: broccoli, cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dry salad dressing together. Add to the vegetables. Chill overnight. Before serving, top with bacon bits.

title: coconut-caramel dessert
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add coconut and chopped pecans. Stir over medium heat until lightly brown.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/3 of cheese mixture over crust, then 1/3 of coconut mix and 1/3 jar of caramel ice cream topping drizzled over the coconut.
Repeat twice.
Cover and freeze 8 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 or 15 minutes before serving.
Serves about 15.

title: squash relish
directions: Shred or grind squash, onions and peppers.
Mix salt in enough ice water to cover squash, onions and peppers.
Let soak for 3 hours.
Rinse off salt water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water, celery seed and turmeric and pour over squash.
Boil for 10 minutes. Pack in hot jars.

title: "bob's" quick corn light bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and shortening.
Pour in a small greased skillet or loaf pan.
Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Stir together cornstarch and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Put into 2 pie shells.
Top with other 2 shells, which have been cut or pricked by fork to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and delicious chocolate mousse
directions: Scald milk.
Pour hot into blender and add other ingredients. Blend.
Pour into small glasses and let solidify in refrigerator for several hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on packages.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
Drain broccoli and combine with cheese spread, sauteed vegetables, undiluted soups and mushrooms.
Fold in cooked rice and turn into 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish, mix sugar and cocoa.
Pour in milk; add margarine.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, until margarine melts.
Stir to mix.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Eat and get fat!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine in iron skillet.
Stir until bubbly in bottom.
Add peanuts.
Cook until spinning thread and begins to darken a little.
Add baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: 2-flavor fudge
directions: Combine in a large saucepan brown sugar, granulated sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and butterscotch morsels.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 2-quart pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Save 1/3 cup of the Blue cheese.
In a small dish, mix remaining Blue cheese and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and cream until creamy.
Add the rest of the cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: microwave cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese together in microwave-safe dish in microwave.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together; add to cheese mixture gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Let stand until firm; cut into squares.
Yields 120 servings. This fudge stays creamy.

title: fuzzy
directions: Drain peaches.
Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
For a sweeter drink, add peach juice.

title: basic meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix together beef, onion, crumbs, egg, ketchup, milk and seasonings.
Mold into a rounded flat loaf in 9-inch pie plate. Spread 2 tablespoons ketchup evenly over top of loaf.
Insert temperature probe and cover with plastic wrap.
Attach cable end at receptacle.
Microwave at High; set temperature at 170°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust with first two ingredients.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, second stick Nucoa and eggs until fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Scatter pineapple over this and sliced bananas next.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Place cherry halves over top.

title: jamaican jungle bread
directions: In large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix banana, pineapple, oil and eggs.
Add to oat mixture.
Stir until liquid is absorbed and mixture is thoroughly moistened. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Glaze if desired.

title: crab linguini
directions: In a skillet combine chicken broth and white wine.
Boil until reduced to 1/3 cup.
Remove from the heat and slowly whisk in half and half and evaporated milk, stirring constantly until blended. Return to the heat and simmer until the mixture is reduced to 1-1/3 cup.
Meanwhile, combine 2 teaspoons softened butter with flour. Slowly whisk into the milk mixture.
Continue stirring until the sauce is thickened and no lumps remain.
Add crab, chopped parsley, chopped green onion, salt, and lemon juice.
Reduce the heat and simmer until the crab is heated through.
Meanwhile, cook linguini according to the package directions.
Toss with 1 tablespoon butter and grated parmesan cheese.
Pour the sauce over the pasta and toss until evenly coated.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate.

title: cranberry honey glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in small pan and cook over low heat, stirring until cranberry sauce is melted. Spoon glaze over chicken or turkey during last 1/2 hour of cooking. Heat and serve remaining sauce with meal.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: Brown vegetables in butter; set aside.
Mix rice and dry soup mix in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top.
Dump vegetables over chicken.
Pour boiling water over all.
Cover very tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° until chicken and vegetables are done (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and green pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas (which have been dipped into hot stock, chicken broth, long enough to soften) in shallow 3-quart buttered casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup broth over layered mixture.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt.
Mix and heat soups; add in order:
soup, then tomatoes.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple-cherry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg. In large bowl, combine cherries and apples.
Add sugar mixture and toss to coat.
Transfer to pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Dot fruit with margarine or butter.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook, peel and slice sweet potatoes into a buttered casserole dish.
Drain and add Mandarin oranges to sweet potatoes.
Mix the other ingredients and bring to a boil in a saucepan.
Pour over potatoes and Mandarin oranges.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbling.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Put all of the above into a blender and blend on high until thick.
Serve over spinach or garden salad with chopped walnuts, mandarin oranges, olives, tomatoes, etc.
Leave in blender until ready to use so you can whip it before you serve it.

title: neptune salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve as a salad on a bed of lettuce, as sandwich filling or with crackers.

title: caldo de pollo(chicken soup)
directions: Wash chicken well.
Skin adds flavor.
Remove if you wish.
Add water to cover well.
Add mint, garlic, onion and salt.
Simmer almost at a boil 1 to 2 hours, then add carrots and zucchini. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
If you wish to add potatoes, boil them separately and add when ready to serve.
Delicious when topped with diced onion and crushed oregano.
Squeeze a bit of lime on top.

title: grape salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Let congeal in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend sour cream, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over top.
May sprinkle nuts on top.
Serves 16.

title: bacon-cream cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Trim ends of bread.
Spread 8 slices with cream cheese and make sandwiches with remaining 8 slices.
Cut sandwiches into 8 small rectangles.
Wrap 1/3 strip of bacon around rectangular sandwich and secure with toothpick.
Place hors d'oeuvres on baking sheet and place under broiler until golden brown; turn over to brown other side.
Makes 64 hors d'oeuvres.

title: peach pie
directions: Sprinkle peaches with sugar and let set awhile.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Use rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Begin and end with flour.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar, raisins or both before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with one layer of graham crackers.

Mix pudding with 3 cups milk until smooth, then add Cool Whip to this mixture. Pour part of Cool Whip and pudding mixture over first layer of crackers, then ice the second layer of graham cracker with chocolate frosting. Pour remaining pudding mixture on top of second layer of crackers. Top off with more iced graham crackers. After top layer of crackers are placed, fill in cracks with chocolate frosting.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugars with oleo.
Add cocoa and eggs; beat well.
Add flour alternately with sour milk.
Beat well; add coffee.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ribbon icebox dessert
directions: Line bottom of square loaf pan using 8 graham crackers.
Put oleo or butter in bowl and mix in powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Slowly beat in the Pet milk.
Spread on crackers in pan. Cover with 8 more graham crackers and chill.

title: sauteed scallops mediterranean style
directions: Cut large scallops in half horizontally.
Rinse under cold water; drain well.
Clean and quarter mushrooms.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet over high heat.
Saute mushrooms 3 to 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to small bowl and reserve.
Whip pan clean.
Dredge scallops in flour with salt and pepper.
Shake off excess flour.
Heat remaining butter and oil over high heat.
Brown butter.
Add scallops in single layer.
Brown on one side for 2 minutes.
Turn. Brown other side 2 minutes.
Scatter shallots over scallops and toss.
Add tomato, garlic, lemon juice and mushrooms (drain mushrooms).
Toss.
Add Marsala.
Heat through.
Transfer to warm plates and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over linguine, if desired. Serves 2.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand at least 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring often. Add all other ingredients. Stir well. Bake at 350 degrees 30-40 minutes.

title: lydia's easy microwave fudge
directions: In large bowl, melt chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in confectioners sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in small pieces and enjoy.

title: fig jam
directions: Combine figs, sugar and gelatin and let stand for about 30 minutes to blend flavors and allow a little liquid to form.
Bring to boiling and cook and stir for about 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place breasts between double layers of wax paper and pound until meat flattens.
Make sure all areas are same thickness. Heat the oil in a pan.
When hot, add chicken, keep flame high cooking each side for a minute or less.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Melt butter in the pan.
Add mushrooms and cook until all moisture evaporates.
Add the shallots, garlic, Marsala, and broth.
Bring to a boil then simmer the sauce until reduced by half.
Spoon over chicken.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli, wash and drain.
Split stalks; place in large saucepan with boiling water and salt.
Cover and cook until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Drain.
Heat garlic and oil in a small pan.
Add broccoli, sprinkle with lemon juice and salt. Cook until broccoli is heated through.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Immediately remove from oven and cover surface of cake with marshmallows.
Set aside 5 minutes.
Pour icing over marshmallow covered cake.
Allow to cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: hearty chicken and rice soup
directions: Combine broth, water, rice, celery and carrots. Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender. Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted. Makes five 1-cup servings.

title: straw stacks
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler.
Add noodles, nuts and potato sticks.
Stir until well coated.
Drop onto wax paper in small stacks.
Let cool.
Serve.

title: yummy meat balls
directions: Mix ground meats, onion, rice, cracker crumbs, egg and seasonings.
Shape into balls, about the size of golf balls, and place in a greased casserole dish.
Pour over tomato soup diluted with water.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon and set aside.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and stir until moistened only.
Bake in two loaf pans for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before turning out on rack.
Freezes well.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Brown hamburger/sausage in skillet.
Melt cheese and soup in saucepan, when melted combine milk, meat and picante sauce.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: divinity candy
directions: For first cooking, mix 3 c. sugar, syrup and 3/4 c. hot water and boil till it makes a good thread. Beat whites of three eggs stiff. Pour slowly into eggs, beating vigorously. Continue beating while mixing 1 1/2 c. sugar and 3/4 c. hot water; boil sugar and water until a hard ball is formed when dropped into cold water. Pour second cooking into first cooking. Beat until it forms a stiff dough. Take peanut butter and mix in butter; mix until smooth. Roll candy out on dough board. Spread with peanut butter mixture. Roll up and cut in slices. use powdered sugar to flour dough board. Makes 3 to 4 pounds of candy.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and nuts.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Break graham crackers and lay on a cookie sheet. Spread margarine mixture over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Let cool and break apart to serve.

title: "perfect" potato soup
directions: Heat butter/oil in large skillet and saute leeks/onions and potatoes until golden brown.
Bring stock to boil and add sauteed vegetables.
Simmer for half hour or until potatoes are soft. Remove vegetables from broth and puree in blender or use potato masher.
Add broth; adjust seasoning.
Serve with chopped parsley.

title: cabbage meal in one
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges and place in greased casserole dish (3-quart).
Mix raw ground beef, rice and onion, oregano between wedges.
Combine tomatoes, water and seasoning and pour over the casserole.
Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop meat and onions.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Roll and refrigerate until needed.

title: white bean mushroom soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook the next day in vegetable stock and sea salt for 2 hours.
To keep the beans from becoming too thick, add water.
Blend the beans until smooth.
Mix together the olive oil, onion, garlic, mushrooms, porcine mushrooms, Madeira and herbs; saute together until the mushrooms release their liquid.
Add the bean mixture and milk.
Simmer for 20 minutes and serve with chopped herbs on top.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets in a saucepan; add sugar and vinegar. Heat to boiling.
Place shelled eggs, beets and onion in a large bowl.
Pour hot beet juice mixture on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 days.
Makes a great side dish for Easter dinner.

title: cabbage and rice
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add chopped cabbage and stir.
Cover and simmer over low heat, about 1 hour or until cooked.
Combine cabbage mixture with hot cooked rice.
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes and tomatoes
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender over medium heat.
Stir in salt, pepper, basil and thyme.
Add tomatoes and potatoes.
Mix gently until coated with seasonings.
Turn into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread a layer of graham crackers. You may have to break some to get an even layer.

title: yellow cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on the box.
Drain oranges and mix in the cake and bake.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers, onion, pepper and carrot in large gallon jar with a good lid.
Add sugar, vinegar and spice.
Shake well and refrigerate.
Shake once each day for the next 4 to 5 days.
Will keep months in fridge (if not eaten first).

title: light as a feather muffins
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in flour and milk.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Bake at 375° in greased muffin tins for 15 minutes.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Blend yogurt, vanilla flavoring, crushed pineapple and orange juice concentrate in a blender. Pour the mixture into small paper cups. Freeze. When the mixture is half frozen, place a popsicle stick in each. To serve, turn cups upside down and run warm water over them until the popsicle slips out.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine gelatin, marshmallows and water.
Stir until dissolved; let cool.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Spread ravioli in casserole dish; brown ground beef and spread over ravioli.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is slightly brown.

title: uncle ben's wild chinese rice
directions: Mix contents of box, soup and water in 2-quart casserole.
Add Chinese vegetables.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake 1 hour 20 minutes at 350°.
You may serve with Chinese noodles and soy sauce.
Chicken or seafood may be substituted.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add soup, water, corn, green peppers and seasonings.
Mix well and simmer 15 minutes.
Fill a 10-inch iron skillet or a 10-inch casserole (3/4 full).

title: jim's homemade chili
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add spices and mix.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and kidney beans. Simmer on low heat for one hour.
Makes approximately 5 quarts.

title: eggless mayonnaise
directions: Measure sugar, salt, mustard, paprika and milk into a bowl. Beat with rotary egg beater to mix well.
Add the oil, a teaspoon at a time, and beat after each addition.
Continue with this until 1/4 of the oil has been added.
Add the vinegar or lemon juice a little at a time and continue beating.
When all of the vinegar or lemon juice has been added, pour the remaining oil slowly, beating all the time.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies; set aside 1/2 cup.
Mix cookie crumbs with melted oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs.
Mix until blended.
Combine pecans and brown sugar in another bowl. Mix well with cinnamon.
Spoon 2/3 of the batter into lightly greased tube pan.
Cover with pecan mix and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and milk, drizzle over top of cake when cool.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and poppy seed, then add liquid ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: ambrosia
directions: Halve all oranges, scoop out orange pulp and squeeze oranges. Discard any seeds.
Open cans of pineapple and pour into bowl with orange pulp.
Coconut must be finely grated for best results, I recommend a food processor.
Stir mixture after each ingredient is added.
Add 2 cups sugar and 1 cup orange juice.
Sugar may be increased or decreased according to taste.
Chill overnight.

title: good chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken (do not coat).
Fry in small amount of oil.
When brown, remove from skillet.
Add onion and tomato puree.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, rosemary and basil if desired.
Add Ragu sauce to make plenty around chicken.
Return chicken to skillet. Cover and simmer over low fire until meat is real tender.
This is also good for pork chops and spare ribs.

title: french onion soup
directions: Add first 5 ingredients together in saucepan.
Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add to broth.
Heat to desired temperature.

title: southwest express chicken salad
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir onion in hot oil until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add chicken, 2/3 cup picante sauce, tomatoes, cumin, salt and oregano.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange lettuce on 4 dinner plates or a large platter. Top with hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with cilantro. Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Let set until it forms own juice.
Boil 7 minutes.
Take off stove and put in 2 large packages of strawberry jello.
Put in jars and seal.

title: coconut cream or chocolate cream pie
directions: In large skillet, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Then add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat; add butter, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue or whipped cream.
(Sprinkle coconut on uncooked meringue for decoration.)

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook egg noodles and drain.
Add together cottage cheese, sour cream, milk, soup mix and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Mix this into the noodles.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with some Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and heat in large pan until Velveeta melts.
Add cooked and drained hamburger.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan with the flour tortillas.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes until heated through.

title: fudge buttermilk cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix well; batter will be thin.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with your favorite frosting.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, soda and salt; mix well. Blend sugars; add margarine and mix.
Beat eggs until fluffy. Add to other mixture.
Add flour, chocolate chips and blend at low speed.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops a little.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and top with chops.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: baked meatball surprise
directions: If using Corn Flakes, crush into fine crumbs.
Mix together all ingredients, except catsup.
Combine thoroughly.
Shape meat mixture into 12 balls, about 2-inches in diameter.
Place in single layer in greased, shallow pan.
Spoon 1 teaspoon catsup over each meatball.
Bake in hot oven at 450° about 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings of 2 meatballs each.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Soak the raisins in hot water for 10 minutes. Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell until firm and light brown at 325° for 40-50 min.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients on high for 30 seconds in a blender.

title: indian meat loaf
directions: Make meat loaf: hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, taco seasoning and onion.
Add enough bread crumbs so it will form a nice loaf. Then add tomato juice, enough to make it runny with a cake like consistency.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until done.
Pour frozen peas onto meat, then pour bag of Tater Tots on top of peas.
Spread cream of mushroom over Tater Tots.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes longer, until everything is hot.

title: chili chips(appetizer)
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Melt Velveeta with meat and add spices. Spread the meat on the cocktail bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle herb and garlic powder as desired.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt together in double boiler the peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
Add noodles, making sure all are coated. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and cool in refrigerator. Makes about 36.

title: beans and beef barbecue
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with celery, onion and bell pepper.
Drain off fat; add tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
In a large casserole, add combined beans, sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Mix and bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Boil to 235° or soft ball stage.
Add nuts and remove from heat.
Stir until it turns sugary.
Pour onto cookie sheet and separate nuts.
Cool.
Makes about 1/3 pound.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Beat until fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
When cool, spread 1 pound can blueberry or cherry pie filling.
Add Cool Whip when serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, buttermilk, vanilla and margarine.
Lastly, add the Bisquick. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into thin, small pieces.
Cook in water until almost done; drain off most of the water, leaving enough to completely cook potatoes.
Add onion.
Reduce heat to simmer; cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture, almost to a boil.

title: sexy chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate and add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook carrots and potatoes for 10 minutes.
Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add carrots, potatoes, peas, onion and celery. Mix soups and broth together and pour over chicken.
Mix together flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over chicken and vegetables. Bake 40 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Finish batter with cold water.
Use extra shortening in skillet.

title: copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until fork tender.
When cool, alternate layers of carrots with pepper and onion slices. Combine Worcestershire sauce and remaining ingredients over heat. Pour sauce over layered vegetables, cover and refrigerate.
Best when allowed to set a few days.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 8-inch pan and chill 1 hour or until set. Cut into squares.

title: morning coffeecake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Arrange frozen bread rolls in pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch pudding, then sprinkle with nuts.
Cook in saucepan until dissolved the butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour mixture over rolls.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Let rise overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to first mixture along with vinegar, butter and boiling water. Cook over low heat until thick, then remove and stir in lemon extract.
Pour into baked pastry shell. Add meringue and brown.

title: bean pot
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: hobo bread
directions: When you were small

title: hamburger soup
directions: Braise hamburger meat and drain excess grease off of meat.
Add all ingredients plus water as needed.
Bring soup to a boil and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oats, syrup and vanilla.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Melt chocolate bits and peanut butter together.
Spread over baked mixture.
When set, cut into bars.

title: mum's pineapple surprise cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening and the sugars.
Add 1 beaten egg, the vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
