Add the can of pineapple with juice and stir in the butterscotch chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: larry's crabmeat dip
directions: Blend all together until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with chips, vegetables or crackers.

title: mom's blue ribbon pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter or margarine.
Mix well.
Add syrup, vanilla and dash of salt.
Add pecans; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.
Roast pecans just until lightly toasted, stirring often, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice apples.
Mix well flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Put in prepared pie crust.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Put on top crust.
Brush with milk and a little sugar.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Season steak with salt and pepper. Place in crock-pot with onion. Pour tomatoes over top. Cook 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: cucumber cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish, hot sauce, minced onions and cucumber; mix well. Makes 2 cups.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, fruits, vegetables and nuts.
Chill and serve. Garnish with leaf lettuce and tomatoes.
Makes 2 entree portions.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Set out a heavy saucepan.
Pour 2 cups fresh raspberries into pan.
Blend in 1/2 cup of sugar.
Blend together to make a paste: tablespoon of cold water and 1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Blend into berry mixture.
Stir constantly and boil over medium heat 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Makes 1 cup.
Can substitute strawberries.
Good over ice cream, angel food cake, etc.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, blend sugar and cream cheese.
Then blend in peanut butter.
Next, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: lemon curd spread
directions: In heavy saucepan beat eggs and sugar.
Stir in lemon juice, butter and lemon peel.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat for 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened (160 degrees). Cover and store in refrigerator.
Yield 1 2/3 cups.
Spread on hot buttered biscuits or toast.

title: fruit-cheese cups
directions: You will need 2 1/8-inch paper cupcake shells.
Mix well cream cheese, lemon juice, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Place one vanilla wafer in each cupcake shell.
Place about one tablespoon of batter on each wafer.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool and remove from shells.
Top with pie filling.
Yields about 48 cups.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: In saucepan melt soup, evaporated milk, chilies, pimentos and Velveeta.
Brown hamburger, add onion, salt, pepper and jalapeno juice.
Cover bottom of 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans with corn tortillas. Cover with meat mixture (1/2 on each).
Cover with another layer of tortillas.
Then cover with cheese sauce (1/2 on each).
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes until cheese sauce starts to bubble.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 2-inch pieces and brown in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Stir in onion soup mix, garlic powder and flour.
Add milk and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Cover and cook on low heat for one hour.
Stir twice while cooking.
If desired, blend in 1/2 cup sour cream and 2 tablespoons sherry.
Heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles. Makes four servings.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Set aside.
Beat sugar and oil on medium speed in medium mixing bowl 2 minutes.
Add egg. Beat until light and lemon colored.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix very well and freeze.
Great for the kids to help make and, of course, eat!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix together eggs, sugar and oil; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: not so spooky spiders
directions: Line baking pan with waxed paper.
In 2 cup microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 2 minutes. Stir.
If chocolate is not completely smooth, microwave an additional 20 to 30 seconds.
Stir.
Add rice cereal and coconut and stir.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper, forming spider body shapes.
Stick 4 noodles into each side of "body" for legs. Add eyes on top of spider.
Refrigerate for about 15 minutes or let set at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Store in covered container.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet; combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Serve.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: summer dessert
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add strawberries. Stir and refrigerate stirring occasionally. When it begins to thicken, fold in Cool Whip.
Leave in refrigerator until jelled. Cut angel food cake in half, crosswise, making two layers. Spread bottom layer with Jello mixture. Add top layer and frost top and sides with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to slice and serve.

title: glazed onions
directions: In 1-inch boiling water, add salt in large skillet.
Cook whole onions, covered, over medium heat about 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.
In large skillet, melt butter with sugar.
Add onions; saute over medium heat, turning until golden brown, about 5 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon grease until tender.
Combine corn, bacon, onion and green pepper in casserole.
Crumble handful of Ritz crackers and stir for thickening.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: paydays
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick melted butter and egg in an ungreased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Put marshmallows on top. Mix syrup, 1 stick butter, peanut butter chips and vanilla. Stir until melted. Then stir in peanuts and Rice Krispies. Pour over cake. Cover and put into refrigerator until cool.

title: chilled marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables in a plastic bag.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar,
oil
and eggs; add dry ingredients, apples, nuts and
coconut.
Mix
thoroughly.
Bake
at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Grease and flour pound cake pan.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Pour crushed pretzels in a
9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour the melted margarine over the pretzels.
Place mixture in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Cool.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, mix chicken, 1/2 of the taco seasoning, 1/2 of the sour cream and 1/2 of the soup.
Add 1 cup cheese to chicken mixture.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine remaining soup, seasoning and sour cream.
Spoon chicken mixture on each tortilla shell; roll up shells.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread remaining soup mixture over tops of rolled up tortilla.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the shells.
Return to oven and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Increase oven to 450°. Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer; blend well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Blend melted chocolate into 1 cup batter.
Pour batter into pan.
Drop chocolate batter into making 5 dropping with knife.
Make marble by cutting through batter.

title: zwiebelrostbraten mit bratkartoffeln(pan-fried sirloin with onion rings served with fried potatoes)
directions: Beat the sirloin. Salt and pepper it. Dip one side of the meat into the flour.
Heat the oil and fry the sirloin with the floured side down first. Brown it on both sides.
Put the meat out of the pan and keep it hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix cheese, Bisquick and pepper.
Fry or boil sausage; mix and drain.
Add sausage to other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place ingredients in order in greased baking dish (10-inch). Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries.
Save a few whole for garnish.
Put half the remaining berries into a saucepan with sugar.
Cut the other berries in half.
Crush the berries in the saucepan with pastry blender or potato masher.
Combine cornstarch with lemon juice and add to the crushed berries.
Cook over low heat,
stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened and become transparent. Add remaining half berries.
Fold in gently.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Chill.

title: yogurt smoothies
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix until smooth.
Pour into a glass and enjoy!

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Prepare rhubarb to boil.
Stir rhubarb and sugar; let stand for 2 or 3 hours.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the jello.
Put into jars and seal.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Trim bread.
Butter one side of bread.
Put 2 layers bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour milk-egg mixture over layer.
Use spatula to push down until milk comes to top.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in saute pan.
Saute mushroom caps, coating well with butter.
Combine remaining butter and the next 6 ingredients until blended.
Place mushrooms on rimmed baking sheet.
Evenly mound filling into each mushroom cavity, pressing lightly.
Sprinkle with pepper and cheese.
Broil about 6 inches from heat source for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: hot fruit crock-pot punch
directions: Heat in crock-pot until hot and steamy.
Makes the house smell great.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the cookies in a large plastic bag, using a rolling pin, or in a food processor.

title: hot chicken salad ii
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and taco seasoning together. Spread on a plate.
Add chopped lettuce, onion and tomatoes.
Top off with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Place taco chips around the edge of plate to use for dipping.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix.
Put in pie plate; fill with ice cream. You can eat it plain or dress it up with fresh peaches.
This recipe can also be frozen (without the fruit) until it is eaten.

title: creamy cheddar spread
directions: In bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in beer or milk.
Add Cheddar cheese and red pepper, beating until well blended.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve as a spread on Triscuits. Garnish with parsley.

title: layered pan salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with dressing and grated cheese.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it comes to a boil. Add peanuts and cook until syrup is light brown or until the peanuts are done.
Remove from heat and add soda.	Beat until soda is mixed well.
Pour in greased pan or foil lined cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended, then eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended.
If necessary, chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: crusty tuna surprise
directions: Combine cheese, soup and milk.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange layers of rice, tuna, parsley and soup mixture. Repeat layering.
Sprinkle flakes or chips over mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: quick 'n cheesy nachos
directions: Microwave Cheez Whiz according to directions on jar.
Place chips on platter.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Pour cheese over top.

title: sourdough bread and starter
directions: Note:
Make this at least 10 days before making bread.
Do not use quick rising yeast.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine flours.
In a large bowl thoroughly mix 2 1/2 cups flour mixture, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup flour mixture.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes. Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into 14 x 9-inch rectangle. Shape into loaves.
Place in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Brush with oil and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
When ready to bake, remove from the refrigerator.
Uncover dough carefully.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
With toothpick, puncture any gas bubbles that may have formed.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and water as needed.
Simmer for awhile until heated all the way through.
Serve over tortilla chips.
Top with grated cheese.

title: powdered sugar
directions: In a blender, process 1 cup granulated sugar and cornstarch together until finely powdered.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Use as you would commercial powdered confectioners sugar.
This homemade powdered sugar comes in handy sometimes.

title: garden zucchini and shrimp
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cook over medium heat; stir occasionally until shrimp turn pink and zucchini are crisp but tender (5 to 8 minutes).
Spoon shrimp, zucchini with butter sauce over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salad
directions: Mix together and place in punch bowl.
Top with 1 bag of Fritos.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Put meat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer beans over meat.
Pour taco sauce over beans. Spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: alaskan blue stew
directions: Cut whale into bite size pieces (including blubber).
Place in an empty, clean gasoline storage tank.
(I'm sure that will be easy to find.)
Add vegetables and cover with water.
Add seasonings.
Cook at 325° for 42 hours, then simmer 6 days. Serves 539,000 people, approximately the population of Alaska.

title: marinade for grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass or plastic dish. Combine marinade ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Grill over hot coals, turning once, until done.
Can be cut into strips and threaded on skewers, then grilled.

title: apple crunchies
directions: In small bowl, mix peanut butter and cereal.
Cube apple and add to mixture.
Toss until cubes are covered.
Yields 1 to 2 servings.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Fold chips into batter with spatula.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: red flannel hash
directions: In skillet, cook potatoes and onions in oil.
Then add corned beef, milk, salt and pepper sauce.
Cook over medium heat until lightly brown, turning occasionally.

title: helen's fruit salad
directions: Pour all or any fruit in a large bowl.
Pour 1 cup of drained juice over the fruit.
Sprinkle the instant vanilla pudding over the top; stir well.
Sprinkle coconut on top of completed salad. Cover with plastic.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
In skillet saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add chicken broth and heat until heated through, stir in rice and chicken.
Remove from heat.
Gently fold in Butterball stuffing, put mixture into greased 11x7x2 baking dish.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare gravy according to package directions.
Spoon gravy over each serving just before serving and top with parsley

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix in order.
Freeze and stir every 2 hours.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up to desired consistency.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and fluffy.
Add sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, lemon juice and melted butter.
Blend well.
Fold in raisins and chopped pecans (or walnuts).
Pour mixture in pastry-lined pie pan.
Garnish top with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water, then add all ingredients except sour cream.
Divide into 2 bowls and refrigerate until partially jelled.
Frost one bowl with sour cream.
Dump second bowl on top of sour cream.
Refrigerate until fully jelled.

title: berry upside-down cobbler
directions: Add sifted dry ingredients alternately into milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour batter into a greased casserole.
Put drained fruit over batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour 1 cup juice over all.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
As it bakes, the crust will rise to the top.
Serve warm with plain or whipped cream.

title: colorful veg-all cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.
(Leftover chopped, cooked ham or sausage can be added.) Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Rub butter over surface of unbaked pie shell.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Combine eggs, cheese, milk, salt, nutmeg and sugar; mix well.
Sprinkle shell with bacon and pierce shell.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in pan with water.
Cover tightly with foil.
Do not vent.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove from oven and drain liquids (don't disturb the ribs, they'll fall apart).
Chill in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours before grilling.
Baste with "My favorite barbecue sauce" to glaze.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Make the pie filling according to the directions on the can. Pour the filling into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on the dry cake mix evenly.
Sprinkle on the coconut and pecans.
Drizzle the melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In plastic bag, mix flour, baking powder, salt, paprika, pepper, cashews and sesame seed.
Rinse chicken in cold water; drain.
Dip into eggs combined with milk.
Allow excess to drip. Shake chicken parts in plastic bag, few at a time until well coated.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan in 400° oven.
Remove pan.
Place chicken in pan, turning so both sides are greased. Bake skin side down in single layer, 20 minutes.
Turn chicken. Bake 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 12 servings.

title: munch-crunch
directions: Mix cereal, nuts and seeds in a large bowl.
Sprinkle mixture with cheese; shake bowl to distribute.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and biscuit mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Yields 15 servings.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Salt both sides
of
meat
with 3 salts.
Place meat on foil and pour liquid smoke around meat.	Seal foil and bake at 275° for 4
hours.
Open
foil
and	pour
barbecue sauce over meat.
Bake 1 hour more with foil open.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onions and saute over low heat.
Add water and chicken bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling.
Stir occasionally until cubes dissolve.
Gradually add noodles and salt; cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes more.
Add milk, cheese and a little pepper.
Cook until cheese melts.
Makes 4 quarts.
Can be frozen.

title: the ultimate cream cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs until light yellow.
Add cream cheese; mix until well blended.
Add sugar and almond extract.
Oil a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Wipe up excess oil with a paper towel.
Pour cream cheese mixture into pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Be sure the cheese cake is not too brown.
Cool.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: pineapple trifle
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Tear or cut cake in 1-inch cubes; set aside.
Combine pudding mix, milk and 1/4 cup reserved juice; mix on low speed 2 minutes.
Whisk in sour cream, then fold in pineapple.
Place half of cake cubes in bottom of serving bowl; drizzle with half of remaining pineapple juice. Pour half of pudding mixture over cake.
Cover pudding with remaining cake.
Drizzle with remaining juice and cover with remaining pudding.
Chill 3 hours, then spread on Cool Whip.

title: chocolate cake with caramel sauce
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and milk. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture and mix well. Stir in vanilla. Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Combine together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Stir in pineapple, carrots, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: ashley's monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in halves.
Shake pieces in a paper bag full of the sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Arrange pieces in a Bundt pan. Melt margarine; add brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour over pieces in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: banana torte
directions: Mix Jiffy cake mix by directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan for 15 to 20 minutes (layer will be thin).
Cool.

title: peach long cake
directions: Mix peaches with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Let stand at room temperature. Sift together the flour and baking powder. Blend in 6 tablespoons sugar, salt and butter.
Combine egg and milk. Stir into flour mixture and blend well. Spread dough into well-greased 9 x 7-inch pan.
You may double the recipe for a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with peaches and juice.
Cream together the butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 6 tablespoons flour.
Drop here and there over peaches. Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Serve with Cool Whip, ice cream or milk on top.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to boil.
Cool.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Spoon into 8 x 8-inch glass pan or a large bowl.

title: double-rich chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour and cocoa.
Mix well and set aside.
With an electric mixer at medium speed, blend sugars and butter, beating to form a grainy paste.
Scrape down sides of bowl. Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fully mixed.
At low speed, add the flour and chips.
Do not overbeat.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes. Immediately transfer cookies to a cool surface.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Heat other ingredients.
Then add drained squash and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips together and beat well for five minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
When done, let sit in pan for five minutes, NO MORE. Turn onto a cake plate.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef, garlic and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce. Mix cheese, egg, seasonings and spinach together in separate bowl. Place 3 uncooked lasagna noodles in center of pan.
Spread noodles with half the cheese and spinach mixture.
Then a layer of sauce, repeat with 3 noodles and rest of cheese mixture.
Top with 3 noodles and remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Mozzarella, if desired.
Pour 1 cup water around edges.
Cover securely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
May serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: chocolate pie(old fashion recipe adapted to microwave)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in microwave dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium-High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring 3 times. (Mixture should be getting thick.)
Stir 3 or 4 tablespoons hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then add yolks to hot mixture. Microwave uncovered on Medium-High for approximately 2 1/2 minutes or until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked crust. Beat whites; add
3 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top and brown in oven.

title: bread and butter pickles(easily refrigerated)
directions: Bring brine to boil and let cool.
Pour over cucumbers.
Put lid on jars; refrigerate.
Shake every day for 5 days.
Keep refrigerated and they will last a year or more.

title: praline strips
directions: Arrange graham crackers in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Place margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Heat until boiling and let boil on low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon over crackers evenly.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cut each cracker in half while warm.
Cut strips in half, if a bite-size is desired.

title: italian corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally, adding reserved liquid if mixture seems dry.

title: mohogany chiffon cake
directions: Combine the boiling water and the cocoa and let it cool.
Set aside.
Sift together in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda and the salt.
Make a well and add the salad oil, egg yolks, vanilla and the cooled cocoa mixture.
Beat until smooth.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar into oil as if creaming sugar; then beat in eggs. Sift dry ingredients and mix together.
Then add carrots.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, slice each layer in half and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: chicken b l t
directions: Boil breasts.
Reduce to low heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes until cooked. Remove, cool and cut up.
Boil chicken water.
Add pasta and cook 10 minutes until firm and tender. Drain well. Cook bacon and drain.
Break into small pieces.
Add pasta to dressing. Toss. Add rest of ingredients and toss to mix.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese set out for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix all together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in crushed pecans.

title: fried chicken for 100
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika together.
Dip cut up pieces of chicken in buttermilk, then dredge in flour mixture. Deep fry at 325° until done.
Drain on paper.

title: mashed sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes until smooth.
Beat in 1/4 cup brown sugar, 6 tablespoons orange juice, 1/4 cup butter, salt, eggs, cinnamon and cloves.
Spoon mixture into buttered, 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with pecan halves.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream in baking dish (2-quart). Melt butter.
Mix with crackers.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.

title: ranch style carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 7 minutes. Cool.

title: orange shake
directions: Pour orange juice into a shaker.
Put powdered milk into shaker too.
Add vanilla and about 4 ice cubes.
Put the top on the shaker tightly.
Shake it like mad.
Pour your shakes into tall glasses.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in a food processor bowl until smooth.
Slowly add carrots (through the feed tube).
When carrots appear to be fully grated, remove lid and add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Replace lid and blend until the dry ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey garlic pork chops
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chops in heavy plastic bag. Refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Broil or grill, turning once after 10 to 12 minutes.
Baste occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: imperial margarine kolach
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball; cover with plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator a few hours or overnight. Roll dough out a little at a time in a small amount of flour.
Cut into squares and fill with your favorite fillings.
Fold 2 of the opposite corners to middle and pinch together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until bottoms are lightly golden.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw the chopped broccoli and drain well.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Add grated cheese on top.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut up stew meat into small chunks.
Add water (enough to cover meat).
Combine tomatoes, onion, salt, Worcestershire, chili powder and bay leaves in pot with meat.
Cover and cook on low-medium until meat is done.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for about 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in the water until tender.
If desired, mash potatoes slightly with
fork to thicken the soup. Add milk, margarine and seasonings.
Heat.
Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Scrape uncooked corn from the cob.
Heat butter until melted. Stir in sugar and flour and remove from heat.
Gradually stir in cream.
Add well beaten eggs, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Fold in corn, stirring until well mixed.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Pour in corn mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all to boil, then simmer 15 minutes and add pieces of pork, beef or chicken.

title: third hand sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Combine sausage with cream cheese and Rotel.
Stir until cream cheese is melted.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine flour and salt; use to coat pork.
Brown pork in shortening in large skillet over medium heat.
Continue cooking 20 minutes, stirring constantly, or until pork is tender.
Always cook pork thoroughly.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and vinegar.
Set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet; bring to a boil, stirring to loosen particles in bottom of skillet.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces.
Place in buttered baking dish and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Add mushrooms.
Blend mushroom soup and liquid from sliced mushrooms.
Pour over steak; cover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix with wire whip or spoon.
Do not use blender.
Keep refrigerated.
Stir well before using.
Flavor improves if made 24 hours before using.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil and boil one minute. Stir in remaining items and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix with fruits and nuts. Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° (slow) for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cook shells according to package directions. Drain and lay on wax paper to prevent sticking. Make Stove Top dressing according to directions, using chicken broth instead of water. To Stove Top, add the meat of 3 chicken breasts which have been cubed. Stuff this into cooked shells. Mix 3 cans of cream of chicken soup with the 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth. Place small amount of sauce in bottom of casserole dish. Place shells in pan and pour the remaining sauce over the top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° in metal pan or 325° in glass dish until top is bubbly.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, onion and Beau Monde together until well blended.
Dice meat, add to mixture and mix well.

title: viva la chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Prepare ingredients as stated.
Butter large oblong casserole dish.
Alternate layers of tortilla squares, chicken, cheeses, soup and salsa, approximately 2 layers.
Save a little cheese for the top.
Best if refrigerated overnight for flavors to mingle.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serve topped with chopped green onions, salsa or avocado pieces or whatever you may choose.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Soak shrimp in ice water in refrigerator.
Drain.
Combine other ingredients and then add shrimp.
Serves 6.

title: bertha eichhorn's foundation sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm water.
Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour to make a batter.
Add yeast and beaten eggs; beat well. Add remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
When light, punch down and let rise again.
Shape as desired:
cinnamon rolls, long johns, etc.

title: honey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill well.
Makes one cup of dressing.
Put 2-3 Tbsp. on each salad serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Brown margarine lightly in skillet to lend a rich flavor. Remove from stove. Stir in sugar and as mixture cools slightly, add eggs beaten together. Add corn syrup and pecans. Pour into one extra-large or two small pie pans lined with uncooked pastry. Bake in moderate oven until mixture sets and the crust browns nicely. Do not over cut.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine or butter, then mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt on low heat, the Hershey bars; stir the Cool Whip into the melted candy bars.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust. Chill overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and place in large bowl along with pimento cheese and cream cheese, broken up into small pieces.
Let sit about 30 minutes.
Add chopped nuts; mix thoroughly and form into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in paprika to desired color and taste.
Keep in refrigerator until 30 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add pineapple, margarine, milk and egg yolks. Cook in heavy pan over medium heat until thick and clear. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with egg white meringue. Bake in 325° oven for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: face paint
directions: Mix shortening, cornstarch, flour and glycerin together until smooth.
Divide mixture into number of different paint colors desired.

title: hawaiian hamburgers(6 servings)
directions: Combine ingredients; form into 6 (4-inch) individual patties. Brown patties in skillet in a little fat.
Pour off fat.
Cover hamburgers with sauce (see below).
Cover and simmer over low heat 15 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine and fold together lemon juice, almond extract, vanilla, Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Chill for 2 to 4 hours.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly into bowl.
Fry the onion in the leftover bacon grease until the onion becomes yellow.
Then, mix in the flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper; blend until smooth.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute; pour over potatoes.
Break the crisp bacon into pieces; add half of it and toss with other ingredients.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Add milk and bouillon cubes.
Cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook broccoli using package directions.
Add broccoli and cheese to soup.
Add water if too thick.
Cook until heated through, stirring frequently.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Make white sauce with butter, flour, salt,
pepper
and
milk;	remove	from heat.
Stir in onions, mayonnaise and beaten eggs.
Carefully stir in broccoli.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake casserole in pan of hot
water at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.	Sprinkle with cheese during final 15 minutes of baking time.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Measure ingredients in a bowl, except baking powder, eggs and milk, making all measurements level.
Mix thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms, onions, garlic and bouillon.
Cook and stir in bread cubes and cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Beat mashed potatoes with a rotary beater.
Mix in the flour and syrup until well blended.
Turn the mixture into a heavy buttered casserole; cover tightly and let cook in a warm oven (lowest heat) 5 hours.
Check occasionally to be sure that it doesn't get too dry.
Add milk, if necessary.
Leave cover off; dot with butter and bake at 350° for 15 minutes at the end of the 5 hours to form a crust on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well by hand.
Form into 2 large or 4 small balls.
Freezes well.
Balls can be rolled in chopped pecans if desired.

title: hearty beef-n-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frying pan, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: egg-stuffed tomatoes(continental egg salad)
directions: Combine eggs, cheese, mayonnaise, chives and mustard and mix lightly.
For each serving, cut one tomato into 6 sections, cutting almost to stem end.
Fill with egg salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy beef jullien
directions: Dredge strips of steak in flour.
Brown carefully in butter. Remove and put in large pot.
Add onions and pepper to pan and saute.
Mix together rest of ingredients but beans.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour or longer.
When ready to serve, add the beans and serve over rice.

title: chicken coronado
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour into casserole. Crumble crackers and mix with margarine.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: polish pierogies
directions: Beat together eggs, water and salt.
Stir in enough flour to form a stiff dough and knead until smooth and elastic.
Set dough aside for an hour and then knead again, using as little flour as needed.
Divide dough into two portions and on a lightly floured surface, roll out one portion to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut into 3 inch circles.
Put a heaping teaspoonful of filling near the center of each circle.
Moisten the edges of dough with a little water, fold dough over filling to make a half moon, pinch the edges together to secure and set aside.
Repeat with second portion of dough.
To cook, carefully slip pierogies, a few at a time, into a large kettle of gently boiling, salted water.
As they rise to the surface (after about 10 minutes), remove with a slotted spoon and drain thoroughly on a wire rack.
Makes about 50.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat; add taco seasoning according to directions on package.
Cool.

title: chicken or pork chops supreme
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan; top each piece of meat with 1/2 slice of cheese; then soup with 1/2 cup of water.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Pork chops take longer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and melted butter into corn. Add eggs to milk and stir in.
Pour into shallow buttered baking pan. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. Stir pudding from the bottom 3 times while it is baking.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Drop each piece into a well buttered Bundt pan.
Mix melted butter with remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture and pour over biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.
Best hot but still great cold.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly. Cover and chill.

title: fruit fondue
directions: Prepare custard according to package directions, using 1 3/4 cups milk and omitting the egg.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Beat custard with electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip with orange flavoring and top with orange peel.
Serve with fruit dippers.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small frying pan melt butter.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until wilted.
In a small bowl, soak bread in milk and break into crumbs.
In a large bowl place mats, vegetable mixture, bread with milk and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and shape into loaf.
Place in shallow pan and bake one hour.

title: cream cheese shrimp pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of pizza pan.
Spread shrimp sauce over cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients (onions, green pepper, olives and shrimp).
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the top. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken-rice salad
directions: Cook Minute rice using chicken broth.
Do not add butter.
Mix all chopped ingredients together with cooked rice.
Chill well.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: *Substitute your favorite cheeses as desired.

title: orange freeze(diabetic)
directions: Put all ingredients in the blender; blend until the ice cubes are pulverized and the drink is foamy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients and make balls the size of a dime.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 300° until lightly brown.

title: sausage scallopini
directions: Cut sausage in pieces about 4-inches long and fry or pan-broil until cooked.
Saute onions and green peppers in oil.
Do not overcook peppers. Add mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer. Cut cooked sausage into bite size pieces and add to sauce.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.

title: the w i v k whilhite and wall burger
directions: Mix together in a bowl the ground beef, chopped onions, Lipton onion soup mix and water or beer.
Form three or four patties, depending on how big your buns are (the hamburger buns, not your personal buns).
Salt and pepper the patties.
At this point, you should be thinking if you washed your hands before you started. It's too late, but remember next time.
You don't know where your hands have been.
Grill the burgers on the barbecue; melt the cheese on the patties as they finish cooking.
Garnish with lettuce, pickles, tomato, sliced onion, mustard and catsup.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix and freeze. Do not thaw to serve.

title: scallops wrapped in bacon
directions: Wrap raw bacon around each scallop.
Stick the toothpick through the scallop to hold on the bacon.
Put on cookie sheet and broil about 20 minutes.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Do not knead.
Mix well all ingredients.
Put in pan; let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: cornmeal dressing(to serve with chicken or turkey)
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Combine with corn bread crumbs, bread cubes and poultry seasoning.
Blend soup and milk; pour over bread mixture and mix lightly.
Makes 8 cups of stuffing or enough for 8 to 10 pound turkey.
If necessary, add more milk so not too dry.

title: wonderful prime rib
directions: Preheat oven to 500 degrees.

Season prime rib with you favorite seasonings. Place in a roasting pan fat side up. Cook exactly 10 minutes per pound. After proper cooking time, turn off the oven and do not open the door for 8 hours. This is perfect for cooking overnight. This is great and you won't be sorry you tried it.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle raisins and nuts in bottom.
Place frozen rolls on top.
Mix sugars and pudding together.
Pour over rolls.
Melt butter and pour over the sugars. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in oven overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on medium heat until thick, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and beaten egg whites last.
Mix all. Bake 1 1/2 hours in oven set at 350°.
Let cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop onion and brown with ground beef.
Drain grease.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into medium baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: apple pie(kansas city style)
directions: Peel and slice apples into large bowl.
Sprinkle orange juice and lemon rind over apples.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour over apples and mix well.
Turn into pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits in it.
Seal and flute edges.
Mix together the sweetened condensed milk (not evaporated) and 1 tablespoon sugar. Brush entire mixture over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Heat oil in large skillet or deep fryer until hot.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Sprinkle Lawry's seasoned salt over chicken.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture until coated.
Fry in oil until chicken floats to top.

title: james a. rhodes' soft sugar cookies(former ohio governor)
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Beat in the eggs. Mix together the whipping cream and vanilla.
Add to the creamed mixture; mix thoroughly.
Add the baking soda and baking powder to 1 cup of flour; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition, scraping the sides of the bowl, and adding enough flour to make a soft workable dough.
Chill dough overnight.

title: cheese filling(use on kolachy dough)
directions: Cream the cheese first, add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter in an iron skillet.
Add bread crumbs and sugar; cook slowly.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Place in buttered pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook in pot over medium heat for 40 to 45 minutes. Stir often to avoid sticking.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a cookie sheet. Flatten and join rolls together. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then cool.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: In bottom of baking dish, melt the butter and oil. Shake chicken in the flour, salt, pepper, garlic salt, marjoram and paprika. Place chicken skin side down. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Turn chicken over and bake another 15 minutes. Dip chicken in the oil mixture from the pan before adding to the flour mixture.

title: lebkuchen(german cookies)
directions: Mix honey, brown sugar and water in pan.
Add butter and boil. Cool.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and spices in bowl.
Stir in almonds, candied and grated orange peel, then honey mixture until well blended.
Divide dough in half.
Roll half of dough on floured surface to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Make 4 lengthwise and 9 crosswise cuts.
Place cut rectangles 1/2 inch apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until pale brown. Remove to cool.
Brush glaze on tops of cookies.
Decorate with almonds and halved candied cherries.
Let stand 1 hour until glaze sets.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Pour in greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top, if desired.

title: guacamole enchantro
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with chips.

title: pasta waldorf salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, but firm.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples and toss.
Stir mayonnaise and sour cream together and combine with all others. Chill.

title: sweet potato casserole(mom always had this for christmas!)
directions: Place in a flat casserole dish.

title: fresh peach and blueberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until partly set.
Arrange fruits in a 1 1/2-quart ring mold or an 8-inch square pan.
Spoon gelatin over fruit. Chill until firm.
Unmold on large platter lined with leaf lettuce. Serve with sour cream dressing.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven at 450°.
Combine baking mix, milk and cheese into soft dough.
Beat vigorously by hand for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto Pam sprayed cookie sheet or muffin tin.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Blend garlic powder with melted butter or margarine.
The minute the biscuits come from the oven, brush with the garlic butter.
Serve immediately.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Combine soup, cheese, chicken and green chiles.
Spread 1/2 cup chicken mixture over bottom of greased 2-quart rectangular dish. Layer 4 of the tortillas, dipping each in enchilada sauce, and 1/3 of the remaining chicken mixture.
Repeat layers 2 more times. Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil; continue baking 15 minutes.
May top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato.

title: "sissie's" apple cinnamon cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar first.
Then mix rest of ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in bread pan.

title: cool cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crisp vegetables.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix on medium heat in 3-quart saucepan white and brown sugar and milk.
Heat mixture for 1 1/2 minutes after it reaches a hard boil (even boil).
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Fluff; mix well and add peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: baskin-robbins chocolate delight
directions: Bottom Layer: Combine the flour, melted margarine, 1/4 cup sugar and nuts.
Press mixture in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake 20 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Let cool.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and bake in two 9-inch pans.
Cook pudding according to package directions.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water (no cold water).
Mix frozen strawberries in Jell-O.

title: crock pickles
directions: Sprinkle pickles with salt.
Cover with boiling water; leave overnight.
Place pickles in crock.
Then mix the mustard, sugar, pickling spice and vinegar.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar each day until seasoned to taste.

title: lazy golompki
directions: Boil cabbage until tender; drain.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish. Brown hamburg; drain off fat.
Stir rice in with hamburg, then spread over cabbage.
In food processor, blend whole tomatoes. Pour blended tomatoes over rice and hamburg mixture.
Cover dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix in order given (eggs, margarine, sugars, vanilla, peanut butter, soda, oatmeal, candy, chips and nuts).
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into 2 frozen pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until set and brown.
Serve plain or with cheese, whipped topping or ice cream.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chalupa
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Place in slow cooker. Cover with water (reduce water slightly if beans are presoaked). Cover cooker.
Cook on high for 5 hours.
Serve in layers of corn chips, meat mixture, cheese, tomato, lettuce and taco sauce. Yields 15 servings.

title: french truffles
directions: Break or chop the chocolate into medium size pieces.
Place it in the top of a small double boiler over hot water on low heat. Cover and let stand until partially melted.
Uncover and stir until completely melted.
Remove the top of the double boiler temporarily.
Add the butter, a few pieces at a time and stir with a small wire whisk after each addition until smooth.

title: three fruit punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine pineapple, orange, cranberry juices and ginger ale.
Stir in starfruit slices. Add ice or ice ring.
Serve chilled.
Yield:
Approximately 20 servings.

title: oatmeal-chocchip cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add and mix flour, soda and salt. Then add chocolate chips and oatmeal. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Pour 1/2 of vanilla wafer crumbs into 9 x 12 casserole dish. Melt oleo and mix with crumbs to make base. Cream sugar and cream cheese in a separate bowl. Mix Dream Whip as directed on package. Combine with cheese mixture and spread 1/2 of this mixture over crumb crust. Carefully spread cherry pie filling over mixture. Cover this with remaining crumbs. Chill until set and ready to serve.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together milk and vinegar. Stir in oatmeal and let stand about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: dr. pepper jello
directions: Dissolve jello in Dr. Pepper, add raspberries and stir until the raspberries separate.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in pineapple, pour into mold and chill until firm.
Mix together sour cream, sugar, marshmallows and lemon juice.
Unmold, top with sour cream mixture.
Great for Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: turkey sausage stuffed hot peppers
directions: Combine sausage, 1 cup cheese, chili powder and onion; mix well.
Make a slit in each pepper from end to end; remove veins and seeds.
Fill peppers with sausage mixture and press slit together. Dip peppers in egg, then in flour and egg again.
Place on baking sheet and bake in preheated 400° oven for about 25 minutes until sausage is done.
Transfer peppers to baking dish and top with salsa, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: potato and hamburger casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish. Brown ground beef with onions.
Place browned ground beef over potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: jal.  rice
directions: Cook rice drain well. Add all ingredients. Stir well while rice is hot.

title: my mom's cheesecake
directions: Melt butter; mix with graham crackers and press on bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Beat 1 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla and cream cheese.
Pour on crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out of oven; let set 30 minutes.
Mix sour cream, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on warm cake; put back in oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Put in fridge when cooled.
Can be served with fresh strawberries or blueberries.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: In a covered container, combine apple cider vinegar, sugar or Splenda and celery seed.
Add cucumber and onion.
Toss to coat with marinade.
Chill at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 side-dish servings.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not beat, just stir until blended.
Bake at 350°.
May be baked in Bundt pan or loaf pan. Test for doneness.

title: harlequin salad
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly blend cream cheese, mayo, lemon juice and salt.
Stir in pineapple, cherries, pecans and apples. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Cook ground beef and onion in a Dutch oven coated with nonstick cooking spray over medium-high heat until ground beef crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain well. Pat with paper towels. Stir stewed tomatoes and next 3 ingredients into skillet. Cook until thoroughly heated. Stir in cooked macaroni. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and serve immediately.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda together; add to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream.
Blend well; spread half of batter in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased. Cream butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together; add nuts.
Mix well.
Spread half of mixture in half of cake.
Cover remaining batter and then put remaining mixture with nuts on top.

title: lazy man's supper
directions: Brown sausage links and drain off grease.
Slice onions, pepper and potatoes.
Put all ingredients in pressure cooker.
Pour in 1 can tomato soup and one can water and pressure for 8 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sue cox's holiday oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters and cut in bite size pieces.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer oysters and crumbs.
Salt to taste.
Top layer is crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cover with milk, soaking until "soggy".
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: extra special dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs, warm milk, salt and flour.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for one minute. Gradually, stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Shape dough into balls and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from draft for 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Roll each ball in 12-inch circle.
Spread butter on circle and roll back up.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: northwest coast salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spoon into a well-greased muffin tin and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: spicy walnut diamonds(microwave)
directions: Blend flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and spices.
Melt butter in a small, glass bowl in microwave on High.
Combine brown sugar and eggs in a large bowl; beat well until blended well.
Add honey, melted butter and flour mixture; mix until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup of medium, chopped walnuts.
Spread mixture evenly in 2 waxed paper-lined dishes.
Sprinkle evenly with 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Cook, uncovered, one at a time in microwave for 6 to 7 minutes on Bake.
Rotate dish once.
Cool; turn out of pan and peel off paper.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Combine undrained crushed pineapple and sugar in a large saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil gently for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add gelatin and stir till dissolved.
Add the cream cheese and stir till mixture is thoroughly combined.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Cover and refrigerate salad for 1 hour.
Fold in apples, nuts and celery.
Gently fold in dessert topping.
Pour into a 2-quart square baking dish.
Cover and chill several hours or until firm.
Garnish with apple slices and sprinkle salad with additional chopped nuts.

title: busy day meal
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish, adjusting the amount to the number of people being served.
Cover with one can of cream of celery soup and one-half can of milk. Arrange pork chops on top and season with paprika.
This may be prepared ahead of time and placed in a timed-oven, if so desired. Bake at about 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy mexican black bean soup
directions: Mince hot chilli pepper in food processor or blender.
Add beans, tomatoes with their liquid, chicken broth and cilantro. Puree.
Transfer to a small pan or the microwave and heat.
Ready to serve in 4 to 6 minutes.

title: herbed chicken wraps
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper if desired. Melt butter in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned. Remove chicken. Cover and refrigerate 15 minutes or up to 24 hours.

title: another carrot salad
directions: Soak raisins in hot water for 30 minutes and drain.
Drain pineapple and add juice to 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Pour over carrots, coconut, raisins, pineapple and lemon juice.

title: biscuit barbecue cups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups. Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in barbecue sauce; add onion and brown sugar. Cook 1 minute to blend flavors, stirring constantly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in salt, 2 quarts water and ice cubes for 3 hours.
Drain well. Thoroughly mix turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed, sugar, 1 cup water and vinegar; heat to boiling.
Add drained vegetables and bring to full rolling boil. Quickly fill hot sterilized jars making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables and seal each jar at once.
Makes 10 pints.

title: custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and hot milk. Pour custard into four individual custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place cups on rack in water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and salt. Blend well.
Add remaining
ingredients and toss.
Chill well. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: lightning squares
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to sugar and eggs. Add melted margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into pan used to melt margarine.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken feed
directions: Melt together oil, butter, seasonings and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cereals, peanuts and pretzels.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Turn with a spoon.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter into 9 x 13 pan. Mix thoroughly. Press mixture firmly and evenly in bottom of pan. Sprinkle in layers of walnuts, chocolate chips and coconut. Pour Eagle Brand sweetened milk over coconut. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: bread and rolls
directions: Heat sugar, milk, oleo and salt together on stove to just a boil.
Take off stove and cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, beaten in yeast cup (yeast dissolved in warm water).
While milk mixture cools.
Add together and add flour (small amounts at a time).
Let raise on stove in warm place until doubled in size.
Knead down; let raise again and then knead and make into shapes (bread or rolls).
Let raise and bake until golden brown at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Butter when hot.

title: marzetti casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Saute pepper, celery and onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together, saving half of cheese for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Makes
layers.
Grease and flour pans.
Cook at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.	Cool completely.

title: easy cream cheese fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy and set aside.
In top of double boiler, melt butter and then add bark.
Heat and stir until melted and smooth.
Pour this over cream cheese and beat about 7 to 10 minutes until glossy.
Stir in nuts of your choice and pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Store this in refrigerator.
Yields 64 (1-inch) pieces.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix salt, barbecue seasons, chili powder and curry powder. Cut away all fat and gristle from strips of meat.
Pound the meat with a meat hammer on a wooden cutting board.
Shake on seasonings as you beat.
Place strips on cookie sheets.
Place in oven for 7 hour on 150° or place under wood stove overnight.
Turning the strips as they dry.
The deer jerky will preserve longer than it will stay around.
This is a very fast mover.

title: lee tuna casserole supreme
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, milk, cheese and dry mustard.
Heat until cheese melts. Combine with tuna and peas.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni; drain and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour remaining ingredients over macaroni.
Stir (add more milk if desired).
Center 4 slices of American cheese on top and spread crumbled potato chips around the edges.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or until nicely browned and bubbling.
Cover when removed from oven to keep hot.

title: sausage bake
directions: Cook sausage and onion together until done. Drain.
Mix Bisquick, 1 egg and milk together and spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle caraway seed on top of batter. Spread sausage mixture on top.
Mix sour cream, remaining egg and salt. Spread on top of sausage mixture.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt butter in large saute pan; saute onion and garlic until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, blending in cream cheese.
Add skim milk as needed and heat through.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, for dipping.

title: pizza
directions: Get a round pan.
Turn the oven on to 55°.
Make crust and put it in the pan.
Pour on the sauce.
Add the meat and cheese and olives.
Cook it for 55 minutes.
If it's not burned, eat it.

title: barbie cups
directions: Press 10 biscuits into muffin tins, making a cup shape.
Brown and drain one pound of meat and stir in 1/2 cup barbecue sauce. Spoon meat evenly into cups.
Sprinkle tops with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Wash and drain kidney beans.
Slice onion over beans.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water and oil.
Pour over beans and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings, depending on size of cans.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place spinach in a large salad bowl.
Add the shredded carrots.
Slice mushrooms and add.
Fry bacon; cool, crumble and add to vegetables.
Add cherry tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add the wine vinegar before serving (use more or less than 3 tablespoons as desired).

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is still hot, prick all over with fork.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand. Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes. Don't overbake. Can be served with bananas and whip cream.

title: rum balls
directions: Line airtight container with wax paper. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine wafers, granulated sugar and walnuts. Add butter and rum. Stir until well blended (mixture will be crumbly). Shape mixture into 1 inch balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Let stand for 1 hour. Reroll balls in powdered sugar before placing in prepared container. Store in refrigerator. The flavor of the rum balls improves after a few weeks' storage. Makes 2-1/2 dozen balls.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fry in small amount of oil until brown. Flip and brown the other side.
Makes 8 patties.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients in mixing bowl, pour into pie shells. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes.
Set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, cinnamon and orange juice.
To that mixture, add potatoes.
Mix well and place in a large baking dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or until set.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add 1 teaspoon sugar. Add to mixture. Blend in the flour. Knead well. Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Remove at least 2 hours before shaping into rolls. Let rolls rise 1 hour. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Scoop melons with melon scooper.
Mix cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and powdered sugar.
Mix over fruit mixture. Very good!

title: spiced nuts
directions: Put aluminum foil in pan and grease.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into pan.
Cook at 250° for 40 minutes.
Keep stirred while cooking.

title: cheesecake cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix to make crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup. Press remainder in an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: goombars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup Pet milk, either in double boiler or in microwave.
If you do it in the microwave, stir it every minute or it will burn.

title: healthy tuna dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gefilte fish
directions: Filet fish but save skin, head and bones.
Combine skin, head and bones with 4 sliced onions and 1 quart water, 2 teaspoons salt and 3/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook over high heat.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in covered jar and refrigerate.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: baked ziti parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large saucepot, brown meat in oil until meat is browned, drain and rinse with hot water to remove fat.
Return to pot, add soup, sauce and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Meanwhile, cook ziti and drain, spoon a thin layer of sauce into 9-inch square baking pan.
Add ziti, top with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 Parmesan, cover with Mozzarella cheese and then the rest of the Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, about 25 minutes until bubbly and browned on top.

title: ranch potato salad primavera
directions: Mix all ingredients together; marinate in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.
If desired, 4 cups cooked pasta may be substituted for potatoes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook diced potatoes and onion until tender (soupy) in just enough water to cover.
Add cubes of cream cheese to potato and onion.
Remove from heat.
Stir until cream cheese is melted.
To potato mixture, add remaining ingredients.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and ending with the flour.
Mix until just blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour and white sugar.
Bring to a boil the oleo, water, cooking oil and cocoa; add to flour mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake.

title: italian sandwiches
directions: Cook ground round.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Add dried onion pieces.
Cook, stirring to make small pieces.
When almost done, sprinkle generously with Worcestershire sauce.
Continue cooking and stirring until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine in order given.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chile rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch or 3-quart baking dish.
Bake in ungreased dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-pecan coffee
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in basket of drip coffee maker or electric percolator.
Place water in pot.
Prepare coffee according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix cake by pkg. directions. Bake and cool. Mix pudding by pkg. directions. Break candy bars and put in a bowl. Crumble cake in another bowl. Layer cake, pudding, cool whip and candy. Add layers until cool whip is on top when finished, garnish with candy chips.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion in margarine. Add soup and paprika.
Warm on very low heat. Add sour cream.
Warm through.
Serve over noodles.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread Marshmallow Creme and cool.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, and cocoa in saucepan until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow and butter, stir until melted.
Pour over crumbs. Place in well buttered dish. Chill and serve.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese in a saucepan.
Stir together the sugar and cocoa.
Add the cheese and margarine to the sugar and cocoa.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and spread evenly in a buttered (for flavor) 9 x 13-inch pan; let cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Yields about 6 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix 1 of each can of frozen juice with water as directed. Pour each juice into an ice tray, setting aside any juice that is left over.
Freeze about 15 minutes.
Before serving, mix second can of lemonade and combine with ginger ale.
In a punch bowl or pitcher, add remaining reconstituted fruit juices and fruit ice cubes.
Makes about 12 to 14 servings.

title: microwavable hot mexican bean dip
directions: In glass serving bowl, cook all ingredients except corn chips on Medium heat (6) for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir once during cooking.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: crunchy butter toffee
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and butter.
Cook to light crack stage (285°).
Test by adding a few drops to water; they will form a pliable ribbon.
Add 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate. Spread half on top; sprinkle with 1/2 cup walnuts.
Cool.
Turn and repeat with remaining chocolate and nuts.
When chocolate has cooled, break toffee into pieces with a small household hammer. Will yield about 2 dozen pieces.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion. Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients except biscuits.
Set aside. Separate each biscuit into 3 thinner biscuits.
Lay each biscuit over a mini-muffin pan.
Press into cup.
Fill with bacon mixture and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut up chicken.
Combine with salt, pepper and water in saucepan.
Boil for 30 minutes and take meat off bones.
Combine rice, chicken and 3 cups of broth and cook for 20 minutes on medium-high, then turn down to low for 15 minutes.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Brown together beef, bacon and onion;
drain
fat.
Add pork and beans, butter beans and kidney beans.

title: tomato relish (green or red)
directions: Grind onions and tomatoes.
Mix in own juices.
Add other ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes until it thickens some.
Heat jars. Pack and seal.

title: ruth's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet.
Drain and set aside.
In same skillet add vegetable oil and heat until hot.
Add macaroni and brown, stirring constantly as to not burn macaroni. Add water to cover macaroni.
Cook until done.
Drain.
Add meat to macaroni; add remaining ingredients and simmer until heated through.

title: mother's meat loaf
directions: Mix all except tomato sauce and form into a loaf. Top with tomato sauce and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed sweet potatoes with sugar, milk, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into buttered casserole.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer each ingredient in casserole dish, saving part of onion rings to crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except pastry shell. Mix well and turn into shell.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.
Garnish as desired.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended. Spread 1/4 on each ham slice and roll up.
Chill several hours. Slice in 1/2-inch slices and arrange on Ritz crackers.

title: tuna hot dish
directions: Mix all together.
Place into buttered casserole dish.
Top with extra noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tofu-vegetable quiche
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Put tofu, eggs, seasoned salt, nutmeg and pepper in food processor or blender and process until smooth (if using blender, add tofu, a quarter at a time, blending after each addition).

title: koosa (stuffed squash)
directions: Cut stems and scoop out seeds of squash and wash.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage soften to room temperature.
Grate cheese; let soften to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together; shape into balls about size of a marble.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown.
These can be made ahead and frozen.
Just let sit on cookie sheet about 15 minutes before cooking.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place half of the chicken in bottom of pie pan.
Top with 1 can of mixed vegetables and 1 can of soup.
Repeat.
Put the second crust on top. Cook in a 350° oven until crust is golden brown, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onions and peppers. Sprinkle 1/3 cup salt. Set aside 1 1/2 hours.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening.
Add brown sugar and eggs, beat well, then add vanilla and nuts.
Mix in flour.
Pour batter into 2 pans, 10 x 7 x 3/4-inch pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chocolate chips over each pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
If you shake pan as batter begins to rise it will make batter fall and become chewy.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: marinated grilled chicken
directions: Tenderize on both sides of chicken breasts and marinate with dressing for 1 to 2 hours. Cook on your grill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes.
