Drain well.
Mix other ingredients with broccoli and put in baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-carb crustless pizza(healthy)
directions: Spray pie pan with nonstick spray.
A glass pie pan is best. Cover bottom of pan with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Put in oven at 350° for approximately 12 minutes or until bubbly and brown on the edges.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Spread pizza sauce on cheese.
Add other ingredients and vegetables of choice (or use them all for a combo).
Cover vegetables with pepperoni.
Cover the top of the pizza with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until the top is golden.
Remove from oven and cool for approximately 5 minutes.
Slide onto a plate. Grab a fork and enjoy.

title: egg casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Lay bread in it.
Layer cheese and bacon.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over bread.
Let sit overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in oven and let get hot.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Chop cabbage into bite-size pieces and place in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Brown meat; drain.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Sprinkle in uncooked rice.
Place meat mixture over cabbage and cover with sauerkraut, tomato sauce and water. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer.

title: broccoli carrot cauliflower salad
directions: Bring vegetables to a boil and drain immediately so they're still crunchy. Let cool. Add onion, olives and Ranch dressing and mix thoroughly. Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, tomatoes, tomato paste, cottage cheese and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Velveeta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Save enough sauce to put on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Slice the Velveeta cheese in thin slices.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Boil whole eggplant until very soft.
Remove pulp from shell. Mash pulp until very fine.
Make a batter of eggs, baking powder, flour, milk and salt. Add eggplant pulp.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into deep hot cooking oil, frying until brown.
Remove. Sprinkle with sugar while hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: aunt lorene's pumpkin dessert ring
directions: Cream the sugar and egg together.
Add other ingredients. Pour into greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: bible verse cake
directions: Mix and bake like a fruit cake.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Can be made ahead.
It keeps very well.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Place steak in Pyrex pan. Pour marinade over to cover.
Add wine.
Top with onions and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 to 45 minutes, depending on size and thickness.
Slice on an angle, thin.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients until well blended, about 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 30 minutes or until filling seems set.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry onion in fat.
Add beef and brown well.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan or casserole dish.
Cover with Potato Topping.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes to brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kelly's tamale pie
directions: Saute hamburger; drain fat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add soup, chili powder, chopped chilies and paprika.
Heat until boiling.
In an 8-inch square pan, arrange pepper rings, top with Mexicorn down the center of the pan.
Fill remaining sides with burger-soup mix.

title: sand tarts(rolled sugar cookies)
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together until smooth and creamy, about 3 minutes with the electric mixer.
Stir in the flour slowly.
When a stiff dough forms, shape into 4 balls.
Roll each one onto waxed paper.
Chill dough a minimum of 2 hours.
Roll dough thin on floured cloth or board.
Cut desired shapes, using cutters dipped in flour.
You may decorate cookies before baking with sprinkles or nuts or both.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: dutch oven doughnuts
directions: Melt Crisco in Dutch oven or large tin can.

When the Crisco is hot, make a hole in the biscuit and drop carefully in the oil. When brown on both sides, remove and place in brown bag filled with either confectioners sugar or a cinnamon/sugar mixture and shake until well coated.
Serve warm or cold.

title: porcelain thumbprints
directions: Cream margarine in small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, beating at medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg white and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add flour to mixture; stirring until blended (dough will be stiff).
Wrap dough in heavy plastic wrap and freeze 10 minutes.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls, place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Press thumb into each.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Combine powdered sugar, cocoa and water; stir well.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoon into each cookie center. Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot, gently mix.
Cover pot and bring to a boil, remove lid.
Cook at high simmer with lid off until most of liquid has boiled away (about 40 minutes).
Cut into serving pieces and serve with steamed rice.
Can be served chilled.

title: almond chicken with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place chicken in baking dish and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Brown almonds in butter. Remove almonds and in the same skillet, saute onion and drained mushrooms. Add lemon juice, sherry and almonds, stirring well. Spoon over chicken pieces. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Spoon over rice on serving platter and place chicken on top.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover for 15 minutes, adding cheese and onion rings.

title: mrs. tom atkinson's sauce hollandaise
directions: In small saucepan, heat butter just to bubbling.
Meanwhile, put egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and cayenne into container of electric blender, cover container and turn blender on high speed.
Remove cover immediately and add hot butter in a steady stream.
To keep, store in refrigerator.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups sauce.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stud oranges with cloves 1/2-inch apart. Place in baking dish in 1/2-inch water. Bake 30 minutes.
Heat cinnamon sticks and cider.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes more.
Place in punch bowl and float oranges on top.
Keep warm until serving time.

title: hunter's marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix salsa and Dijon mustard.
Marinate chicken breasts overnight.
Cook on gas or charcoal grill until done.

title: baked ziti
directions: Fry ground beef and sausage together; drain grease.
Cook ziti until done; drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in 13 x 9-inch baking dish at 400° for 30 minutes.
Grated cheese may be added before or after baking.

title: pork chops and macaroni and cheese
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cook macaroni and drain. Cut onion, green pepper and celery.
Mix with macaroni.
Mix milk and tomato sauce together.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Layer cheese over mixture.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
Sprinkle paprika and a little salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour on one side and 1/2 hour on the other side or until pork chops are done.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: crispix treats
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate and peanut butter together.
Pour over cereal in a huge bowl.
Mix well.
Dump into big brown paper bag.
Add the sugar and shake, shake, shake until cereal is well coated.
Serve.
A favorite of children.

title: josephine's fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit and mix.

title: grandma's mincemeat
directions: Combine all ingredients in large heavy pan.
Simmer very gently for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Sufficient for 5 (9-inch) pies.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown beef and salt lightly.
Mix other ingredients and add to browned beef.
Heat thoroughly and serve on hamburger buns.

title: beans and ham hocks
directions: Pick through beans to remove bad or split ones and then wash them.
Put on the cook pot and add 5 quarts of water.
Add beans and ham hocks and cook on medium for 3 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
When water turns milky or beans thicken, dish is ready to serve.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Cream part of the cocoa-sugar mixture with butter or margarine.
Blend in vanilla and half of milk.
Add remaining cocoa-sugar mixture and blend well.
Add remaining milk and beat to desired spreading consistency.
Frosting for two 9-inch layers.

title: coconut on a cloud
directions: Mix
flour,
butter and nuts like a pie crust and press into 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Wash bulgur.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Add chopped vegetables and mix well.
Add olive oil, lemon juice and salt. Refrigerate at least 1 hour to allow the bulgur to soak and absorb the juice.
Serve over fresh lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Roll cookies into crumbs (including filling).
Mix with butter and press into pan.
(Reserve some crumbs for top.) Mix pudding, milk and
cream
cheese.
Mix
until
pudding
like; spread
over cookies.
Spread
La
Creme topping over top and sprinkle a few cookie crumbs on top.
Chill and serve.

title: cavetelli and broccoli soup
directions: Slice potatoes in half and steam for 20 minutes.
When potatoes are easily pierced with a fork, remove and let cool.
Peel and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place cubes in a mixing bowl.
Add celery, eggs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add mayonnaise and mix thoroughly by hand.
Serve each person about 1/2 cup potato salad on a bed of lettuce.
For best results, refrigerate salad a few hours before serving.

title: all-day apple butter
directions: Place apples in slow cooker.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt; pour over apples and mix well.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for 9 to 11 hours or until thickened and dark brown, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into containers.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Place butter and vanilla in bowl.
Blend about 2 minutes with mixer.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar; continue beating for 1 minute.
Add eggs; beat for 30 seconds.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually add dry ingredients until thoroughly mixed, about 1 minute.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheets, about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar while still hot.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together in a large saucepan until soft ball stage.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Chop bacon
into small pieces before frying.
Fry bacon crisp; do	not
drain.
Stir
dry	ingredients
over bacon and cook, stirring until thickened.
Good served over lettuce.

title: thumbprint cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add cream cheese and vanilla. Add flour gradually and beat until you can form the dough into balls about the size of walnuts. Place on a cookie sheet and press thumb in center. Put small amount of jelly (guava is good) in each center. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes. Cookies do not brown. This recipe can also be put through a cookie press, chilled, rolled and cut into shapes.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Oil and flour pans.
Makes 3 small loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Dice 2 to 3 large stalks rhubarb.
Place in large saucepan with about 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil and add 1 cup sugar.
Cook rhubarb to mush, then add 1 large box strawberry gelatin.
Bring to a boil.
Add 3 cups of sliced, fresh strawberries.
Remove from heat immediately.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into 2 cooked pie shells. Let cool and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; drain well.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Place mixture into buttered 10-inch pie pan and form crust.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Pour off drippings.
Stir into tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano, garlic powder, minced garlic and salt.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Spread meat filling over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine Mozzarella cheese, paprika and parsley.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes until cheese melts.

title: pudding delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into balls; brown on both sides in small amount of shortening.
Then add the rest of can of soup along with 1 cup water over top of the balls.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes on low heat.

title: fine crumb pie shell
directions: Combine cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Spread in 8 x 9-inch cake pan, pressing firmly onto sides and bottom of pan. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8. Calories per serving 8.

title: hawaiian ham kabobs
directions: Alternate ham, pineapple and green pepper on skewers.
Grill or broil slowly, brushing generously with barbecue sauce and turning frequently.
Push off onto a fluffy bed of rice.
Pass heated barbecue sauce to use over kabobs and rice if desired.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place vegetables in shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and place in refrigerator for 6 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: barbecued pork steak (or ribs)
directions: Brown meat and remove from pan to a roaster or covered casserole.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat and bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Can use less meat and cut sauce in half.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt chocolate.
Spread evenly in pan.
Melt white chocolate and mix with peanut butter.
Pour over chocolate and swirl through with a knife.
Let harden.
Cut into small pieces.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in 13x9 inch pan as directed on box.
While cake bakes; mix 1/2 can of coconut cream with can of eagle brand milk.
Set aside, when cake is done, poke holes in hot caked with a straw or chop stick.
Pour coconut mixture over hot cake.
let cool completely.
Mix remaining coconut with thawed cool whip. spread over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for meat in baking dish.
Lay chicken or chops on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: golden corn dressing
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in butter over low heat until onion is tender.
Add thawed shredded potatoes and broth. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over bread cubes and corn.
Add salt, pepper and eggs.
Stir gently to blend.
Stuff turkey.

title: elegant cream puffs
directions: Prepare Anginetti by slicing off top.
Drain pineapple, leaving a little juice.
Mix topping with cream cheese.
Add pineapple and stir.
Spread generous amount of mixture on bottom of Anginetti.
Place top on.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut shrimp to bite size pieces.
Combine shrimp, celery, onion, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Spread out in a buttered casserole dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and add onion, cheese and pimento.
Put 2 tablespoons butter on top and sprinkle with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix 8 Tbsp sugar and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
Stir together remaining dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, turning to cook all sides.
Lift out with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Roll hot fritter in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place on serving platter.

title: caribou (modern)(huron)
directions: Chop onions and carrots.
Marinate meat 3 hours in a mixture of oil, vegetables and pepper.
Turn meat every 30 minutes.
Dry meat and insert slivered garlic into meat.
Flour and place in roasting pan with fat.
Roast at 500° for 30 to 40 minutes (rare) or 45 minutes (medium).

title: al's survival sandwich
directions: Mix tuna with mayonnaise until mushy (not runny).
Add in potato chips and chopped onions.
(Tomatoes may also go well.) Top with pepper if desired.
Eat alone or on bread.

title: five day pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cucumbers and onion. Be sure sugar and spices are thoroughly dissolved (especially the sugar).
Pack
cucumbers
and onions alternately in jars. Pour liquid
mixture in jars.
Seal and place in refrigerator for 5 days.

title: corned beef and sauerkraut balls
directions: Chop onions and parsley fine.
Break corned beef into small chunks.
Add these to shortening.
Cook until onions are almost tender.
Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add drained sauerkraut and mustard.
Cool.
Shape mixture into small cocktail size balls.
Use enough additional flour to coat the balls.
Dip into beaten egg. Coat finally with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or fry until crisp and brown.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix together.
Spread on halved muffins.
Freeze 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out; cut into quarters and put in plastic bag. When ready to serve, bake at 350° until bubbly about 10 minutes.

title: escalloped potatoes and wieners
directions: Pare and slice potatoes very thin.
Cut wieners into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, wieners and celery in a greased (I use margarine) 8-cup baking dish.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well, then add (set aside) sifted ingredients.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour in an 8 x 6 x 2-inch casserole dish. In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, water and cinnamon.
Pour over margarine in casserole dish.
Add blueberries, spreading on top. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
Mix with potatoes.
Stir in butter, sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Beat well. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta primavera casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Spoon into greased 14 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Saute zucchini, red peppers, mushrooms and scallions in large skillet for 3 or 4 minutes. Add tomatoes. Spoon over pasta.
Place flour in the skillet.
Blend in milk. Add broth, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens; add spinach and pour over vegetables. Cover; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mary ann's cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add shortening.
Mix well.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet; sprinkle with cornmeal on the bottom.
Pour in batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown at 425°.
Yield:
12 to 16 generous slices.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard. Stir until cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside.
Cut the broccoli into bite size pieces.

In a nonstick wok or large nonstick skillet, warm the oil over medium heat, until hot, but not smoking. Add the vegetables and stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender and onion begins to brown, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir the cornstarch mixture again and pour it into the wok.
Stir in the beef, peanuts, red pepper flakes and black pepper.
Stir-fry until the sauce thickens and the beef is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
If necessary, reduce the heat to keep the sauce from evaporating. Serves 4.

title: toll house walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy; add flour and sugars and beat well.
Blend in margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Can be served with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Place pork chops in casserole with a slice of onion on each chop.
Mix brown sugar and catsup and pour over chops.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: quick brunch strata
directions: Butter an 8 x 10-inch (or larger) casserole pan.
Place 4 slices of bread in bottom of dish (cut bread to fit, if necessary). Butter bread slices lightly.
Place an even layer of lunch meat or combination of 2 lunch meats (ham and turkey are very good) over bread.
Place cheese slices over meat.
Spread remaining bread slices with mayonnaise and place, mayonnaise side down, over cheese.
Beat eggs into milk and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven and place tomato slices on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and corn syrup in microwave-safe glass bowl.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes on High until mixture is bubbly and peanuts are brown.
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir in quickly. Mixture will be foamy.
Pour into baking pan.
Cool at least 15 minutes, then break apart.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and form into small balls (about walnut size).
Lay on cookie sheet covered with wax paper to FREEZE separately. (Then put in plastic bag to store in freezer until ready to use.) Place frozen balls on ungreased pan. Bake 400 degrees 15-20 minutes.
Great snack...breakfast or anytime!
Makes approximately 48 balls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Add sherbet to ginger ale.
Cut strawberries in quarters and add.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Add eggs, salt and milk to the flour to make a thin batter. Slice apples thin and add to the batter.
Fry in deep fat. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: grandma's cream cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, buttermilk, extract and vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Delicious with icing or without, served with applesauce, fresh strawberries or peaches. Also good just plain.

title: corn bread
directions: Make pan of corn bread; let cool.
Fry bacon and onion and drain.
In a big bowl break up corn bread; add bacon and onion. Add tomatoes and mix well.
Put into baking dish.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in oven on about 350°.

title: forever amber
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in rectangle pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool; make small balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: porketta seasoning
directions: Instead of 1 (1 ounce) square baking chocolate, use 3 tablespoons cocoa plus 1 tablespoon margarine.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In a large bowl combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients (except for the kisses).
Mix on lowest speed until a dough forms.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls using a rounded teaspoon of dough for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven and top each cookie with a kiss.
Press down firmly, so cookie cracks.
Enjoy!

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine salt, sugar, oleo, corn syrup and vanilla in a large, heavy pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for only 5 minutes.
Stir slowly.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir well.
(This will foam up and get lighter in color.)
Pour over corn; stir to cover well.
Put into large, flat pans.
Place in a 250° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn 2 times with spatula.
Cool. Store in tight containers or plastic bags.
May be kept in freezer but keeps well many days at room temperature.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Put pineapple sherbet in punch bowl, pour liquid over it and stir.
Add ice cubes with cherries frozen in them.

title: laurie's fudge
directions: Bring to a boil on medium heat, sugar and Pet milk.
Let boil 10 minutes, stirring continuously.
Take off heat.
Add butter and chocolate chips, stirring constantly, then add Marshmallow Creme. Stir until smooth.
If desired, add nuts (about 3/4 cup) and vanilla.
When it's smooth, pour into lightly greased Pyrex dish and place in refrigerator until firm.
I use 1 (13 x 9-inch) or 1 (11 x 8-inch) Pyrex dish.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in
boiling
water
for
to 7 minutes. Drain; combine eggs,
soup
and oregano.
Stir in tomatoes and cooked broccoli.
Put
in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and
bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: salmon stew
directions: In saucepan mash the salmon until it is in small pieces. Cover with water, salt, butter, and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add peeled, diced potatoes, cook until tender.
Add milk until the broth is white.
Slightly mash the potatoes.
Serve with oyster crackers.
Serves 4.

title: ground turkey patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray Teflon frying pan with Pam and add mixture to pan with a tablespoon.
Shape into patties. Cook on medium to low heat until done.

title: grilled corn
directions: Heat oil in frying pan. Add and slowly brown corn. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes over low heat.
If you have hot peppers, they are good in this dish.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix.
Makes 1 quart and stores well in refrigerator.

title: faye's coconut custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Stir in eggs. Add milk and coconut; then stir in vanilla and margarine. Bake in 2 unbaked shells at 350° until set, probably 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add gelatin and strawberries.
Pour into baked pie crust and cool.
Add whipped cream on top when ready to serve.

title: easy buns
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Meanwhile, mix 2 cups warm water, 1/2 cup sugar, melted shortening and salt.
Add the yeast.
Add gradually the flour. Beat well.
Put on floured board and knead for 5 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Roll into buns and place on greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Butter tops.

title: creamy ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: skillet corn
directions: Lightly fry beef and onions in oleo until beef begins to curl. Stir in flour and cold milk; cook, stirring until thickened.
Add corn and heat until hot.
Add cheese and green pepper.
Stir over low heat just until cheese melts.
Serve at once over buttered toast triangles or toast cups.

title: frontier chowder
directions: Brown ground beef with chili powder and garlic.
Pour off excess drippings.
Stir in soups; gradually stir in water.
Add corn.
Heat, stirring now and then.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix and cook slowly over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add Rice Crispies, 1/2 cup pecans.
Roll in balls and then roll in coconut.

title: quahog chowder
directions: Chop quahog meat, set aside.
Cut the salt pork into small squares.
Fry until golden brown.
Remove pieces; save.
Add chopped onion until golden brown.
Chop potatoes and simmer in milk.
Add quahogs and simmer in salt pork fat and onions.
Add quahog juice, potatoes and milk.
Heat and add dollop of cream. Serve with 1 teaspoon of butter.
Better the next day.

title: corn oysters
directions: Combine egg yolks, corn, salt and pepper in a bowl. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over moderately high heat. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into skillet and cook until golden brown on underside.
Turn and brown.
Remove and keep hot while cooking rest.
Add more oil as needed. Serves 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a preheated baking sheet for 50 to 55 minutes.
If it is cooking or browning too fast, turn temperature down to 300° and finish cooking until the pie is jelled.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold in topping.
Pour into prepared crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and white sugar with oil and eggs.
Sift flour with soda and add to sugar mixture; add vanilla, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza of sorts
directions: Layer in order given. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover the last 5 minutes. (Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.)

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook until clear.
Cool. Add 1 can of oranges, drained, and 1 can of the oranges, not drained.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey in pan with chopped onion.
Add Lea & Perrins (about 3 shakes).
Add dash of garlic, onion and pepper.
Drain when finished cooking.
Into crock-pot, put 1/2 bottle of chili sauce, 1 can tomato soup, mustard, vinegar and 1 tablespoon Lea & Perrins.
Add ground beef or turkey with onion. Put 1 stick butter on top.
Cover and put on low for 4 to 6 hours or high for 1 to 2 hours (stir occasionally).
Season to taste as cooking.
Good after hot, but better the longer it's in.

title: three vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each vegetables separate according to directions on package.
Place each vegetable in baking dish (9 x 14-inch).
Pour undiluted soup and Cheez Whiz over vegetables.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, so the soup and Cheez Whiz have melted into the vegetables.
Pour onions over all about 10 minutes before taking from oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine and oil in skillet.
Add chopped stems and minced onions and saute for a few minutes.
Add bread crumbs and Swiss cheese and keep stirring until cheese melts.
Place mixture into mushroom caps.
Place caps on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rigatoni supreme
directions: In a saucepan, over medium heat, saute onion in olive oil until pale gold.
Add sausage and saute for a few minutes.
Add mushrooms, basil and red wine.
Allow wine to evaporate.
Add tomatoes and let mixture simmer for 8 minutes.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste and remove from heat.

title: taffy tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together in medium size bowl.
Set aside.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat at medium speed for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat 3 1/2 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: souse meat
directions: Cook pig ears, feet and snoots with piece of onion.
Put spices and cloves in small cheesecloth bag (tie bag). Drop in pot with meats. Add red pepper flakes.
Let cook until meat falls off the bones.
Cool. Pull all meat off bones.
Chop meat and onion in a large bowl.
Add sage, pepper, nutmeg, Accent, more red pepper to taste, salt if needed, vinegar and hot sauce. Mix thoroughly and pour into loaf pans.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Two hours ahead, add garlic to French dressing.
Remove garlic before mixing all ingredients cold.

title: noodles with sour cream
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
Do not blanch.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add 1 tablespoon scallions, sour cream, cheese, nutmeg and noodles.
Toss lightly to coat noodles.
If mixture is dry, add more sour cream or some milk. Turn into a heated bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Serve immediately.

title: hershey's deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted margarine, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, beating well with a spoon. Combine dry ingredients and add gradually. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: busy day barbecue ribs
directions: Will need a 2 quart Pyrex dish.
Microwave oven makes this dish a snap!!

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Shake oil, vinegar, cheese and basil in tightly covered container.
Pour over tortellini.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours, or until chilled.
Toss with remaining ingredients. Serve with freshly ground pepper and additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: gayle's pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 crusts.
Chill.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Set aside nuts, sugar and cinnamon.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into pan and cook over low heat, stirring continually.
Dough is done when it forms a ball.
Let cool, then knead.
(May be colored with food coloring at time of mixing.)
Store in an airtight container.
Fun to play with but not to eat!

title: baked italian spaghetti
directions: Partially brown beef in fat, add onions and peppers.
Continue to cook until they become glazed and beef is browned on all sides. Add seasonings, tomato puree, catsup and water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat is suspended throughout mixture and flavors are well blended.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water about 20 minutes; drain.
Mix spaghetti and sauce.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Note: Casserole can be frozen.

title: sun-dried tomatoes, olive and basil sauce
directions: Combine sun-dried tomatoes, tomato oil, olives, basil, lemon zest, garlic, pepper, Brie and olive oil in a large serving bowl. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 4 hours.
Cook pasta; drain and immediately toss with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: apple square tarts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, baking soda, cinnamon, flour and nuts.
Blend together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out; let cool about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.
Cut in 3 x 3-inch squares.

title: gooey almond cake
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch iron skillet with aluminum foil.
Combine margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add salt, almond extract and vanilla.
Stir in flour until ingredients are well blended.
Pour batter into foil-lined skillet.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and almonds over top of batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until cake is golden brown and tests done.
Cool and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate until chilled, then form into balls and roll in chopped pecans. Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate.

title: smoky salmon cheese spread
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons liquid.
Flake.
Combine reserved liquid with salmon, cream cheese, onion and liquid smoke. Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours.
Form mixture into a log 6 to 8-inches long.
(Optional:
Sprinkle with parsley and form pimiento into small bow for garnish.)
Serve with crackers. Makes 1 1/2 cups.
I usually double recipe.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir in.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Yummy!

title: hot dog chili
directions: Peel onions and chop very fine.
Heat shortening in large skillet and cook onions until limp.
Add ground beef; cook until brown.
Put through food processor (meat should be ground very fine).
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Serve with hot dogs and onions.
May be frozen.

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Wonderful with vegetables prepared around hollowed out rye bread loaf which has been filled with the dill dip.

title: baby food pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pout in round tube pan.
Cook for one hour at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and run water over them.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: banana frostee
directions: Peel banana and place in container of electric blender.
Add dry milk powder, water and chocolate extract.
Process until smooth.
Add ice to make 2 cups. Process until smooth.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken, salt and onion.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Layer the broccoli, chicken, sauce and bread crumbs.
For sauce, mix together soup, mayonnaise, evaporated milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Mix together in separate bowl: honey, sugar, egg, Crisco and lemon extract.
Add flour mixture to honey mixture and work together.
Mix well. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll out thin.
Cut with cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir boiling water into gelatin 2 minutes, or until dissolved.
In a separate bowl, mix ice cold water and ice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened. Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes, or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain.
Gently cook beans in about 2 quarts water until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add more hot water if necessary to keep beans covered.
Drain beans and save some of the liquid.
Mix beans with all other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
Add some of the saved liquid if beans become dry while cooking.

title: crab toast appetizers
directions: Beat cheese, butter and mayonnaise until smooth;
blend in crab meat.	(May be made ahead and refrigerated.) Spread on each toasted muffin half.
Bake	in a 350° oven for 5 minutes, then broil several
minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly. Cut each into quarters; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Brown onion in butter until golden.
Mix with remaining ingredients until blended.
Roll into balls. Brown in same skillet.
When all are browned add a small amount of hot water to skillet to loosen drippings.
Return meatballs to skillet and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: easy rump roast
directions: Place roast in a Dutch oven; sprinkle with soup mix and pour in beef broth.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.
